obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (37429)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37429&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Manipur Land Revenue`
  line `and Land Reforms Act, 1960.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of the Union territory of Manipur except the hill areas thereof.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date as the Administrator may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, appoint; and different dates may be appointed for different areas and for different provisions of`
  line `this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (37430)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37430&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Administrator" means the Administrator of the Union territory of Manipur;`
  line
  line `(b) "agriculture" includes horticulture, the raising of annual or periodical crops or garden`
  line `produce, dairy farming, poultry farming, stock breeding and grazing and pisciculture;`
  line
  line `(c) "basic holding" means land used for agricultural purposes which is equal to 2.5 acres in area;`
  line
  line `(d) "commencement of this Act", in relation to any provision, means the date specified in respect`
  line `of that provision in a notification under sub-section (3) of section 1;`
  line
  line `(e) "competent authority", in relation to any provision, means any officer appointed by the`
  line `Administrator to be the competent authority for the purposes of that provision;`
  line
  line `(f) "deputy commissioner" means the deputy commissioner of the district and includes any officer`
  line `appointed by the Administrator to exercise and perform all or any of the powers and functions of a`
  line `deputy commissioner under this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) "family", except in Chapter XI, means, in relation to a person, the wife or husband of such`
  line `person, his children, grand-children, parents and brothers, and in the case of a joint Hindu family, any`
  line `member of such family;`
  line
  line `(h) "family holding" means land used for agricultural purposes which is equal to 7.5 acres in area;`
  line
  line `(i) "Government" means the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(j) "hill areas" means such areas in the hill tracts of the Union territory of Manipur as the`
  line `Administrator may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare to be hill areas;`
  line
  line `(k) "holding" means a parcel of land separately assessed to land revenue;`
  line
  line `(l) "improvement", in relation to any land, means any work which materially adds to the value of`
  line `the land and which is suitable to the land and consistent with the character thereof, and includes--`
  line
  line `(i) the construction of tanks, wells, water channels and other works for the storage, supply`
  line `and distribution of water for agricultural purposes or for the use of man and cattle employed in`
  line agriculture;
  line
  line `(ii) the construction of works for the drainage of land or for the protection of land from floods`
  line `or from erosion or from other damage by water;`
  line
  line `(iii) the preparation of land for irrigation;`
  line
  line `(iv) the conversion of one-crop into two-crop land;`
  line
  line `(v) the reclaiming, clearing, enclosing, levelling or terracing of land used for agricultural`
  line purposes;
  line
  line `(vi) the erection on land or in the immediate vicinity thereof otherwise than on the village`
  line `site, of a building or house for the occupation of the tenant, his family and servants or of a cattle`
  line `shed, a storehouse or other construction for agricultural purposes or of any building required for`
  line `the convenient or profitable use or occupation of the land; and`
  line
  line `(vii) the renewal or reconstruction of any of the foregoing works or such alterations therein or`
  line `additions thereto as are not of the nature of ordinary repairs;`
  line
  line `(m) "land owner", in relation to any land, means a person who acquires rights of ownership in`
  line `respect of such land under sub-section (1) of section 99 and includes the successors-in-interest of such`
  line person;
  line
  line `(n) "minor" means a person who is deemed not to have attained majority under the Indian`
  line `Majority Act, 1875 (9 of 1875);`
  line
  line `(o) "Official Gazette" means the Manipur Gazette;`
  line
  line `(p) "pay", "payable", and "payment", used with reference to rent, include "deliver", "deliverable"`
  line `and "delivery";`
  line
  line `(q) "person under disability" means--`
  line
  line `(i) a widow;`
  line
  line `(ii) a minor;`
  line
  line `(iii) a woman who is unmarried or who, if married, is divorced or judicially separated from`
  line `her husband or whose husband is a person falling under (iv) or (v);`
  line
  line `(iv) a member of the Armed Forces of the Union;`
  line
  line `(v) a person incapable of cultivation by reason of physical or mental disability;`
  line
  line `(r) "personal cultivation" with its grammatical variations and cognate expressions means`
  line `cultivation by a person on his own account--`
  line
  line `(i) by his own labour, or`
  line
  line `(ii) by the labour of any member of his family, or`
  line
  line `(iii) by servants or by hired labour on wages payable in cash or in kind but not as a share of`
  line `produce under his personal supervision or the personal supervision of any member of his family;`
  line
  line `Explanation I.--Land shall not be deemed to be cultivated under the personal supervision of a`
  line `person unless such person or member resides in the village in which the land is situated or in a nearby`
  line `village, within a distance to be prescribed, during the major part of the agricultural season;`
  line
  line `Explanation II.--In the case of a person under disability, supervision by a paid employee on`
  line `behalf of such person shall be deemed to be personal supervision;`
  line
  line `(s) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(t) "public purpose" includes a purpose connected with settlement of land with cultivators, tenants`
  line `ejected as a result of resumption, landless agricultural workers or co-operative farming societies;`
  line
  line `(u) "rent" means whatever is lawfully payable, in cash or in kind or partly in cash and partly in`
  line `kind, whether as a fixed quantity of produce or as a share of the produce, on account of the use or`
  line `occupation of land or on account of any right in land but shall not include land revenue;`
  line
  line `(v) "tenant" means a person who cultivates or holds the land of another person under an`
  line `agreement, express or implied, on condition of paying therefor rent in cash or in kind or delivering a`
  line `share of the produce and includes a person who cultivates or holds land of another person on payment`
  line `of "lousal" or under the system generally known as 'bhag', 'adhi' or 'barga';`
  line
  line `(w) "village" means any tract of land which before the commencement of this Act was recognised`
  line `as or was declared to be a village under any law for the time being in force or which may after such`
  line `commencement be recognised as a village at any settlement or which the Administrator may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, declare to be a village;`
  line
  line `(x) "year" means the agricultural year commencing on such date as the Administrator may, in the`
  line `case of any specified area, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (37431)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Power to create, alter or abolish districts, sub-divisions, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37431&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Administrator may, with`
  line `the previous concurrence of the Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, divide the territories`
  line `to which this Act extends into one or more districts, and may similarly divide any district into`
  line `sub-divisions and tehsils, and may alter the limits of, or abolish, any district, sub-division or tehsil.`
  line
  line `(2) The districts, sub-divisions and tehsils exiting at the commencement of this Act shall continue`
  line `respectively to be the districts, sub-divisions and tehsils under this Act unless otherwise provided under`
  line `sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (37432)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Appointment of revenue officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37432&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The Government or such officer as may be authorised by the`
  line `Government in this behalf, may appoint the following classes of revenue officers, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) deputy commissioner;`
  line
  line `(b) additional deputy commissioner;`
  line
  line `(c) director of settlement and land records;`
  line
  line `(d) sub-divisional officers;`
  line
  line `(e) extra-assistant commissioners;`
  line
  line `(f) survey and settlement officers;`
  line
  line `(g) assistant survey and settlement officers;`
  line
  line `(h) sub-deputy collectors;`
  line
  line `(i) revenue inspectors;`
  line
  line `(j) amins;`
  line
  line `(k) such other village officers and servants as may be appointed by rules made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (37433)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Deputy Commissioner and certain other revenue officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37433&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Each district shall be placed`
  line `under the charge of a deputy commissioner who shall be in charge of the revenue administration of the`
  line `district and exercise the powers and discharge the duties of the deputy commissioner under this Act or`
  line `any other law for the time being in force and shall exercise so far as is consistent therewith such other`
  line `powers of superintendence and control within the district and over the officers subordinate to him as may`
  line `from time to time be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The additional deputy commissioner shall exercise all such powers and perform all such duties of`
  line `the deputy commissioner or other revenue officer as the Administrator may specify by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(3) Each sub-division shall be placed under the charge of a sub-divisional officer.`
  line
  line `(4) The extra-assistant commissioners shall exercise all such powers and perform all such duties of`
  line `the deputy commissioner or other revenue officer as the Administrator may specify by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(5) Each tehsil shall be placed under the charge of a sub-deputy collector.`
  line
  line `(6) The duties and powers of the sub-divisional officers, the sub-deputy collectors and other revenue`
  line `officers shall be such as may be imposed or conferred on them by or under this Act or any other law in`
  line `force for the time being or any general or special order of the Administrator published in the Official`
  line Gazette.
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (37434)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Settlement officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37434&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The officers specified in terms (c), (f) and (g) of section 4 shall have power`
  line `to take cognizance of all matters connected with the survey of land and the settlement of revenue rates`
  line `and the preparation and maintenance of land records and other registers and shall exercise all such powers`
  line `and perform all such powers and perform all such duties as may be prescribed by any general or special`
  line `order of the Administrator published in the Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (37435)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Subordination of revenue officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37435&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `All revenue officers shall be subordinate to the`
  line `Administrator and all revenue officers in the district or a sub-division shall be subordinate to the deputy`
  line `commissioner or the sub-divisional officer, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (37436)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Combination of offices.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37436&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `It shall be lawful for the Administrator to appoint one and the same`
  line `person to any two or more of the offices provided for in this Chapter, to make any appointment by virtue`
  line `of office and also to confer on any officer of the Government all or any of the powers and duties of any of`
  line `the revenue officers including the deputy commissioner.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (37437)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Notification of appointments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37437&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `All appointments made under this Chapter except appointments`
  line `of revenue inspectors and village accountants and other village officers and servants shall be notified in`
  line `the Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (37438)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title Seals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37438&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The Administrator shall, from time to time, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify`
  line `the revenue officers who shall use a seal and also the size and description of the seal which each such`
  line `officer shall use.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (37439)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Title of Government to lands, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37439&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) All lands, public roads, lanes and paths and bridges,`
  line `ditches, dikes and fences on o beside the same, the beds of rivers, streams, nallahs, lakes and tanks, and`
  line `all canals and water courses, and all standing and flowing water, and all rights in or over the same or`
  line `appertaining thereto, which are not the property of any person, are and are hereby declared to be the`
  line `property of the Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Unless it is otherwise expressly provided in the terms of a grant made by the Government, the`
  line `right to mines, minerals and mineral products shall vest in the Government, and it shall have all the`
  line `powers necessary for the proper enjoyment of such rights.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any property or any right in or over any property is claimed by or on behalf of the`
  line `Government or by any person as against the Government and the claim is disputed, such dispute shall be`
  line `decided by the deputy commissioner whose order shall subject to the provisions of the Act, be final.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person aggrieved by an order made under sub-section (3) or in appeal or revision therefrom`
  line `may institute a civil suit to contest the order within a period of six months from the date of such order,`
  line `and the decision of the civil court shall be binding on the parties.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (37440)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Right to trees, forests, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37440&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The right to all trees, jungles or other natural products growing`
  line `on land set apart for forest reserves and to all trees, brush wood, jungle or other natural product, wherever`
  line `growing, except in so far as the same may be the property of any person, vests in the Government, and`
  line `such trees, brush wood, jungle or other natural product shall be preserved or disposed of in such manner`
  line `as may be prescribed, keeping in view the interests of the people in the area with regard to the user of the`
  line `natural products.`
  line
  line `(2) All road-side trees which have been planted and reared by or under the orders or at the expense of`
  line `the Government and all trees which have been planted and reared at the expense of local authorities by the`
  line `side of any road belonging to the Government vest in the Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (37441)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Assignment of land for special purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37441&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Subject to rules made in this behalf under this Act,`
  line `the deputy commissioner may set apart land belonging to the Government for pasturage for the village`
  line `cattle, for forest reserves or for any other purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (37442)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Allotment of land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37442&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The deputy commissioner may allot land belonging to the Government`
  line `for agricultural purposes or for construction of dwelling houses, in accordance with such rules as may be`
  line `made in this behalf under this Act; and such rules may provide for allotment of land to persons evicted`
  line `under section 15.`
  line
  line `(2) The Administrator shall have power--`
  line
  line `(a) to allot any such land for the purpose of an industry or for any purpose of public utility on`
  line `such conditions as may be prescribed, or`
  line
  line `(b) to entrust the management of any such land or any rights therein to the Gram Panchayat of the`
  line `village established under any law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (37443)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Unauthorised occupation of land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37443&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who occupies or continues to occupy any`
  line `land belonging to Government without lawful authority shall be regarded as a trespasser and may be`
  line `summarily evicted therefrom by the competent authority and any building or other construction erected or`
  line `anything deposited on such land, if not removed within such reasonable time as such authority may from`
  line `time to time fix for the purpose, shall be liable to be forfeited to the Government and to be disposed of in`
  line `such manner as the competent authority may direct:`
  line
  line `Provided that the competent authority may, in lieu of ordering the forfeiture of any such building or`
  line `other construction, order the demolition of the whole or any part thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) Such trespasser shall also be liable by way of penalty to pay a sum which may extend to six times`
  line `the annual assessment on such land as may be specified by the competent authority and such sum shall be`
  line `recoverable in the same manner as an arrear of land revenue.`
  line
  line `(3) Upon payment of the penalty referred to in sub-section (2), the trespasser shall have the right of`
  line `tending, gathering and removing any ungathered crops.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (37444)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Liability of land to land revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37444&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) All lands, to whatever purpose applied, are liable to`
  line `payment of land revenue to the Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Administrator may exempt any land from the liability to such payment by means of a special`
  line `grant or contract or in accordance with any law for the time being in force or the rules made under this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (37445)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Alluvial lands.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37445&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `All alluvial lands, newly formed islands, or abandoned river beds, which vest`
  line `under any law for the time being in force in any holder of land shall be subject in respect of liability to`
  line `land revenue to the same privileges, conditions and restrictions as are applicable to the original holding by`
  line `virtue of which such lands, islands or river beds vest in the said holder, but no revenue shall be leviable in`
  line `respect of any such lands, islands or river beds unless the area of the same exceeds one acre.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (37446)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Land revenue in case of diluvion.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37446&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Every holder of land paying land revenue in respect thereof`
  line `shall entitled, subject to such rules as may be made in this behalf, to a decrease of assessment if any`
  line `portion thereof, not being less than one acre in extent, is lost by diluvion.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (37447)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Assessment of land to land revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37447&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The assessment of land revenue on any land shall be`
  line `made or deemed to have been made with respect to the use of the land--`
  line
  line `(a) for purposes of agriculture,`
  line
  line `(b) for industrial or commercial purposes,`
  line
  line `(c) as sites for dwelling houses, and`
  line
  line `(d) for any other purpose.`
  line
  line `(2) Where land assessed for use for any one purpose is diverted to any other purpose, the land revenue`
  line `payable upon such land shall, notwithstanding that the term for which the assessment may have been`
  line `fixed has not expired, be liable to be altered and assessed at a different rate in accordance with rules made`
  line `under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (37448)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Diversion of land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37448&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person holding land for any purpose wishes to divert such land or`
  line `any part thereof to any other purpose except agriculture, he shall apply for permission to the competent`
  line `authority which may, subject to the provisions of this section and to the rules made under this Act, refuse`
  line `permission or grant it on such conditions as it may think fit.`
  line
  line `(2) Permission to divert may be refused by the competent authority only on the ground that the`
  line `diversion is likely to cause a public nuisance or that it is not in the interest of the general public or that the`
  line `holder is unable or unwilling to comply with the conditions that may be imposed under sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(3) Conditions may be imposed on diversion for the following objects and no others, namely, in order`
  line `to secure the public health, safety and convenience, and in the case of land which is to be used as building`
  line `sites, in order to secure, in addition, that the dimensions, arrangement and accessibility of the sites are`
  line `adequate for the health and convenience of occupiers or are suitable to the locality.`
  line
  line `(4) If any land has been diverted without permission by the holder or by any other person with or`
  line `without the consent of the holder, the competent authority, on receiving information thereof, may impose`
  line `on the person responsible for the diversion a penalty not exceeding one hundred rupees, and may proceed`
  line `in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (1) as if an application for permission to divert had been`
  line made.
  line
  line `(5) If any land has been diverted in contravention of an order passed or of a condition imposed under`
  line `any of the foregoing sub-sections, the competent authority may serve a notice on the person responsible`
  line `for such contravention, directing him, within a reasonable period to be stated in the notice, to use the land`
  line `for its original purpose or to observe the condition; and such notice may require such person to remove`
  line `any structure, to fill up any excavation, or to take such other steps as may be required in order that the`
  line `land may be used for its original purpose, or that the condition may be satisfied. The competent authority`
  line `may also impose on such person a penalty not exceeding one hundred rupees for such contravention, and`
  line `a further penalty not exceeding four rupees for each day during which such contravention continues.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--"Diversion" in this section means using land assessed to one purpose for any other`
  line `purpose, but using land for the purpose of agriculture where it is assessed with reference to any other`
  line `purpose shall not be deemed to be diversion.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (37449)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Remission or suspension of revenue on failure of crops.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37449&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The Administrator may, in`
  line `accordance with the rules made in this behalf under this Act, grant a remission or suspension of land`
  line `revenue in years in which crops have failed in any area.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (37450)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Responsibility for payment of land revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37450&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The following persons shall be primarily`
  line `liable for the payment of land revenue assessed on land, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the person to whom the land belongs; and`
  line
  line `(b) the tenant or any other person in possession of the land, provided that such tenant or other`
  line `person shall be entitled to credit from the owner of the land, for the amount paid by him.`
  line
  line `(2) Where there are two or more persons liable to pay land revenue under sub-section (1), all of them`
  line `shall be jointly and severally liable for its payment.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (37451)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Receipt for land revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37451&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Every revenue officer receiving payment of land revenue shall, at`
  line `the time when such payment is received by him, give a written receipt for the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (37452)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Definitions of “revenue survey”, “settlement” and “term of settlement”.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37452&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `The operations`
  line `carried out in accordance with the provisions of this Chapter in order to determine or revise the land`
  line `revenue payable on lands in any local area called a "revenue survey", the results of the operations are`
  line `called a "settlement" and the period during which such results are to be in force is called the "term of`
  line `settlement".`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (37453)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Inquiry into profits of agriculture.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37453&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) As soon as may be after the commencement of this`
  line `Act, the Administrator shall take steps to institute and shall cause to be constantly maintained, in`
  line `accordance with rules made under this Act, an inquiry into the profits of agriculture and into the value of`
  line `land used for agricultural and non-agricultural purposes.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of determining the profits of agriculture, the following matters shall be taken into`
  line `account in estimating the cost of cultivation, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the depreciation of stock and buildings;`
  line
  line `(b) the money equivalent of the labour and supervison by the cultivator and his family;`
  line
  line `(c) all other expenses usually incurred in the cultivation of the land which is under inquiry; and`
  line
  line `(d) interest on the cost of buildings and stock, on all expenditure for seed and manure and on the`
  line `cost of agricultural operations paid for in cash.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (37454)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Revenue survey.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37454&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Whenever the Administrator thinks it expedient so to do, he may, with the`
  line `approval of the Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct the revenue survey of any local`
  line `area with a view to the settlement of the land revenue and to the preparation of a record of rights`
  line `connected therewith or the revision of any existing settlement or record of rights.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (37455)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Power to require assistance from landholders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37455&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `A survey officer deputed to conduct or take`
  line `part in any revenue survey may, by special order or by general notice to be published in the prescribed`
  line `manner, require the attendance of holders of lands to assist in the measurement or classification of the`
  line `lands to which the revenue survey extends and, when hired labour is employed for purposes incidental to`
  line `the revenue survey, may assess and apportion the cost thereof on the lands surveyed, for collection as land`
  line `revenue due on such lands.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (37456)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Survey numbers and villages.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37456&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the rules made in this behalf under this Act, the`
  line `survey officer may--`
  line
  line `(a) divide the lands to which the revenue survey extends into survey numbers and group the`
  line `survey numbers into villages; and`
  line
  line `(b) recognise the existing survey numbers, reconstitute them or form new survey numbers.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (37457)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Division of survey numbers into sub-divisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37457&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `The survey officer may sub-divide survey`
  line `numbers into as many sub-divisions as may be required in the manner prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (37458)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Determination of revenue-rates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37458&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `The Administrator may at any time direct the determination`
  line `or the revision of the revenue-rates for all lands in any area of which a revenue survey has been made.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (37459)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Preparation of statistical and fiscal records.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37459&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty of the survey officer or the`
  line `settlement officer on the occasion of making or revising a settlement of land revenue to prepare a register`
  line `to be called the "settlement register", showing the area and assessment of each survey number, with any`
  line `other particulars that may be prescribed, and other records in accordance with such orders as may from`
  line `time to time be made in this behalf by the Administrator.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (37460)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Revenue-rates how determined.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37460&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of determining the revenue-rates, the`
  line `settlement officer may divide any area into units and in forming such units, he shall have regard to the`
  line `physical features, the agricultural and economic conditions and trade facilities and communications; and`
  line `shall then determine the revenue-rates for different classes of lands in each unit in the manner and`
  line `according to the principles prescribed and in particular, in the case of agricultural land, to the profits of`
  line `agriculture, to the consideration paid for leases, to the sale prices of land and to the principal monies on`
  line `mortgages and in the case of non-agricultural land, to the value of the land for the purpose for which it is`
  line held.
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (37461)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Publication of table of revenue-rates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37461&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) The settlement officer shall prepare a table of`
  line `revenue rates in the prescribed form and publish it in the prescribed manner for the prescribed period.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person objecting to any entry in the table of revenue-rates may present a petition in writing to`
  line `the settlement officer within the prescribed period and the settlement officer shall consider such`
  line `objections after giving a hearing to the objector.`
  line
  line `(3) The settlement officer shall submit the table of revenue-rates to the Administrator together with a`
  line `summary of objections, if any, his decisions on such objections and a statement of the grounds in support`
  line `of the proposals.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (37462)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Confirmation of the table of revenue-rates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37462&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Administrator may confirm the table of`
  line `revenue-rates submitted to him by the settlement officer with such modifications, if any, as he may`
  line `consider necessary.`
  line
  line `(2) The table of revenue-rates confirmed under sub-section (1) shall be finally published in the`
  line `Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (37463)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Rates of revenue to form part of settlement register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37463&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `The table of revenue-rates published`
  line `under section 34 shall be incorporated in and form part of the settlement register of the village.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (37464)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Introduction of revenue-rates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37464&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `When the revenue-rates are determined under this Chapter in`
  line `respect of any area, such rates shall take effect from the beginning of the year next after the date of final`
  line `publication of the table of revenue-rates under section 34.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (37465)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Duration of revenue-rates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37465&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the table of revenue-rates for any area has been finally`
  line `published, the rates specified therein shall remain in force for a period of thirty years.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) revenue-rates may be altered or revised in any year after the expiry of every ten years from the`
  line `date on which the table of revenue-rates was introduced, in such manner and to such extent as may be`
  line prescribed;
  line
  line `(b) When the circumstances of a local area are such that a fresh determination of the`
  line `revenue-rates is in the opinion of the Administrator inexpedient, he may extend the term of settlement`
  line `by such further period as he may think necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (37466)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Assessment on holdings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37466&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) The settlement officer shall calculate the assessment on each`
  line `holding in accordance with the revenue-rates confirmed and finally published under section 34 and such`
  line `assessment shall be the fair assessment.`
  line
  line `(2) The settlement officer shall have the power to make fair assessment on all lands whatsoever to`
  line `which the revenue survey extends, whether such lands are held with liability to pay full land revenue or`
  line `land revenue at concessional rates or are held revenue-free.`
  line
  line `(3) The fair assessment of all lands shall be calculated in accordance with rules made in this behalf`
  line `and having regard to the following principles, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) no regard shall be had to any claim to hold land on privileged terms;`
  line
  line `(b) regard shall be had in the case of agricultural land to the profits of agriculture, to the`
  line `consideration paid for leases to the sale prices of land and to the principal monies on mortgages, and`
  line `in the case of non-agricultural land, to the value of the land for the purpose for which it is held;`
  line
  line `(c) where any improvement has been effected at any time in any holding held for the purpose of`
  line `agriculture by or at the expense of the holder thereof, the fair assessment of such holding shall be`
  line `fixed as if the improvement had not been made.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (37467)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Additional assessment for water advantages.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37467&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this`
  line `Chapter, the Administrator may direct that any land in respect of which the rate of revenue has been`
  line `determined shall be liable to be assessed to additional land revenue during the term of settlement for`
  line `additional advantages accruing to it from water received on account of irrigation works or improvements`
  line `in existing irrigation works completed after the table of revenue-rates came into force and not effected by`
  line `or at the expense of the holder of the land.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (37468)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Continuance of survey operations and rates in force at commencement of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37468&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Chapter, all survey operations commenced under any`
  line `law for the time being in force and continuing at the commencement of this Act shall be deemed to have`
  line `been commenced and to be continuing under the provisions of this Chapter, and all revenue-rates in force`
  line `at such commencement shall be deemed to have been determined and introduced in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this Chapter and shall remain in force until the introduction of revised revenue-rates;`
  line `and such revised revenue-rates may be introduced at any time, notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `section 37.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (37469)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Power of deputy commissioner to correct errors, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37469&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) The powers and duties exercisable`
  line `by the officers referred to in section 6 may also be exercised, during the term of settlement, by the deputy`
  line `commissioner or such other revenue officer as may be specified by the Administrator for the purpose by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(2) The deputy commissioner may at any time during the term of settlement correct any error in the`
  line `area or the assessment of any survey number or sub-division due to a mistake of survey or arithmetical`
  line `miscalculation:`
  line
  line `Provided that no arrear of land revenue shall become payable by reason of such correction.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (37470)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Preparation of record of rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37470&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty of the survey officer to prepare a record of`
  line `rights for each village showing the area of each survey number and other particulars and any other record`
  line `or register, in accordance with the rules made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (37471)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Publication of the record of rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37471&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a record of rights has been prepared, the survey`
  line `officer shall publish a draft of the record in such manner and for such period as may be prescribed and`
  line `shall receive and consider any objections which may be made to any entry therein or to any omission`
  line `therefrom during the period of such publication.`
  line
  line `(2) When all objections have been considered and disposed of in accordance with the rules made in`
  line `this behalf, the survey officer shall cause the record to be finally published in the prescribed manner.`
  line
  line `(3) Every entry in the record of rights as finally published shall, until the contrary is proved, be`
  line `presumed to be correct.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (37472)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Jurisdiction of civil courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37472&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `The civil courts shall have jurisdiction to decide any dispute to`
  line `which the Government is not a party relating to any right or entry which is recorded in the record of`
  line rights.
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (37473)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Correction of bona fide mistake in register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37473&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `The survey officer may, on application made to`
  line `him in this behalf or on his own motion, within one year from the date of final publication of the record of`
  line `rights, correct any entry in such record which he is satisfied has been made owing to a bona fide mistake.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (37474)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Register of mutations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37474&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be maintained for every village a register of mutations in`
  line `such form and in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person acquiring by succession, survivorship, inheritance, partition, purchase, mortgage, gift`
  line `or otherwise any right in land or, where such person acquiring the right is a minor or otherwise`
  line `disqualified, his guardian or other person having charge of his property, shall report his acquisition of`
  line `such right to the competent authority within three months from the date of such acquisition and such`
  line `authority shall give at once a written acknowledgement in the prescribed form for such report to the`
  line `person making it.`
  line
  line `(3) The competent authority shall enter the substance of every report made to it under sub-section (2)`
  line `in the register of mutations and also make an entry therein respecting the acquisition of any right of the`
  line `kind mentioned in sub-section (2) which it has reason to believe to have taken place and of which a report`
  line `has not been made under the said sub-section and, at the same time, shall post up a complete copy of the`
  line `entry in a conspicuous place in the village and shall give written intimation to all persons appearing from`
  line `the record of rights or the register of mutations to be interested in the mutations and to any other person`
  line `whom it has reason to believe to be interested therein.`
  line
  line `(4) Should any objection to any entry made under sub-section (3) in the register of mutations be made`
  line `either orally or in writing to the competent authority, the particulars shall be entered in the register of`
  line `disputed cases and the competent authority shall at once give a written acknowledgement in the`
  line `prescribed form for the objection to the person making it.`
  line
  line `(5) The objections made under sub-section (4) shall be decided on the basis of possession by the`
  line `competent authority and orders disposing of objections entered in the register of disputed cases shall be`
  line `recorded in the register of mutations by the competent authority.`
  line
  line `(6) After the entries in the register of mutations have been tested and found correct, the entries shall`
  line `be transferred to the record of rights and shall be certified by such officer as may be prescribed in this`
  line behalf.
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (37475)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Penalty for neglect to furnish information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37475&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `The deputy commissioner may, if he is of opinion`
  line `that any person has wilfully neglected to make the report required by section 46 within the prescribed`
  line `period, impose on such person a penalty not exceeding twenty-five rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (37476)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Assistance in preparation of maps.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37476&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the rules made under this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) any revenue officer may, for the purpose of preparing or revising any map or plan required for`
  line `or in connection with any record or register under this Chapter, exercise any of the powers of the`
  line `survey officer under section 27 except the power of assessing the cost of hired labour; and`
  line
  line `(b) any revenue officer not below the rank of sub-divisional officer may assess the cost of the`
  line `preparation or revision of such maps or plans and all expenses incidental thereto and such of costs and`
  line `expenses shall be recoverable in the same manner as an arrear of land revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (37477)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Certified copies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37477&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `Certified copies of entries in the record of rights may be granted by such`
  line `officers and on payment of such fees as may prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (37478)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Maps and other records open to inspection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37478&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `Subject to such rules and on payment of such`
  line `fees, if any, as may be prescribed, all maps and land records shall be open to inspection by the public`
  line `during office hours, and certified extracts therefrom or certified copies thereof may be given to all persons`
  line `applying for the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (37479)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Power to transfer duty of maintaining maps and records to settlement officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37479&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `When a local`
  line `area is under settlement, duty of maintaining the maps and records may, under the orders of the`
  line `Administrator, be transferred from the deputy commissioner to the settlement officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (37480)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Determination of village boundaries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37480&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `The boundaries of villages, survey numbers,`
  line `sub-divisions and fields shall be fixed and all disputes relating thereto shall be determined by survey`
  line `officers or by such other officers as may be appointed by the Administrator for the purpose, in accordance`
  line `with the rules made in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (37481)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Effect to settlement of boundary.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37481&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) The settlement of a boundary under this Chapter shall be`
  line determinative--
  line
  line `(a) of the proper position of the boundary line or boundary marks, and`
  line
  line `(b) of the rights of the landholders on either side of the boundary fixed in respect of the land`
  line `adjudged to appertain, or not to appertain, to their respective holdings.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a boundary has been so fixed, the deputy commissioner may at any time summarily evict`
  line `any landholder who is wrongfully in possession of any land which has been adjudged in the settlement of`
  line `a boundary not to appertain to his holding or to the holding of any person through or under whom he`
  line claims.
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (37482)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Construction and repair of boundary marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37482&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `It shall be lawful for any survey officer`
  line `authorised in this behalf to specify or cause to be constructed, laid out, maintained or repaired, boundary`
  line `marks of villages or survey numbers or sub-divisions and to assess all charges incurred thereby on the`
  line `holders or others having an interest therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (37483)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Description of boundary marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37483&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `The boundary marks shall be of such description and shall be`
  line `constructed, laid out, maintained or repaired in such manner and shall be of such dimensions and`
  line `materials as may, subject to rules made under this Act, be determined by the deputy commissioner or`
  line `other officer appointed for the purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (37484)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Responsibility for maintaining boundary marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37484&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `Every landholder shall be responsible for`
  line `the maintenance and good repair of the boundary marks of his holding and for any charge reasonably`
  line `incurred on account of the same by the revenue officers in case of alteration, removal or disrepair. It shall`
  line `be the duty of the village officers and servants to prevent the destruction or unauthorised alteration of the`
  line `village boundary marks.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (37485)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Deputy commissioner to have charge of boundary marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37485&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `After the introduction of survey`
  line `and settlement in a district, the charge of the boundary marks shall devolve on the deputy commissioner,`
  line `and it shall be his duty to take measures for their construction, laying out, maintenance and repair`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (37486)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Penalty for injuring boundary marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37486&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `Any person wilfully erasing, removing or injuring a`
  line `boundary mark shall be liable to such penalty not exceeding fifty rupees as the competent authority may`
  line impose.
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (37487)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Land revenue to be first charge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37487&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `Land revenue assessed on any land shall be the first charge`
  line `on that land and on the crops, rents and profits thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (37488)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Payment of land revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37488&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `Land revenue shall be payable at such times, in such installments, to`
  line `such persons, and at such places, as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (37489)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Arrear of land revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37489&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any installment of land revenue or part thereof which is not paid`
  line `on the due date shall become an arrear of land revenue and the persons responsible for the payment`
  line `become defaulters.`
  line
  line `(2) A statement of account certified by the sub-deputy collector shall, for the purpose of this Chapter,`
  line `be conclusive evidence of the existence of the arrear, of its amount and of the person who is the defaulter:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall prejudice the right of such person to make payment`
  line `under protest and to question the correctness of the account in separate proceedings before the competent`
  line authority.
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (37490)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Recovery of arrears.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37490&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `An arrear of land revenue may be recovered by any one or more of the`
  line `following processes, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) by serving a written notice of demand on the defaulter;`
  line
  line `(b) by distraint and sale of the defaulter's movable property, including the produce of the land;`
  line
  line `(c) by the attachment and sale of the defaulter's immovable property.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (37491)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Notice of demand.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37491&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `The form and contents of the notice of demand and the officers by whom`
  line `such notice shall be issued shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (37492)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Distraint and sale of movable property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37492&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `(1) The distraint and sale of the movable property of`
  line `a defaulter shall be made by such officers or class of officers, in such manner and in accordance with such`
  line `procedure, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall be deemed to authorised the distraint or sale of any property`
  line `which, under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), is exempt from attachment or sale in`
  line `execution of a decree or of any article set aside exclusively for religious use.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (37493)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Sale of immovable property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37493&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the deputy commissioner is of opinion that the`
  line `processes referred to in clauses (a) and (b) of section 62 are not sufficient for the recovery of an arrear, he`
  line `may, in addition to or instead of any of those processes, cause the land in respect of which such arrear is`
  line `due to be attached and sold in the prescribed manner.`
  line
  line `(2) The deputy commissioner may also cause the right, title and interest of defaulter in any other`
  line `immovable property to be similarly attached and sold.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (37494)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `Notice of sale.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37494&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `(1) Before effecting the sale of any land or other immovable property under the`
  line `provisions of this Chapter, the deputy commissioner or other officer empowered in this behalf shall issue`
  line `such notices and proclamations, in such form, in such manner and containing such particulars, as may be`
  line `prescribed; the notices and proclamations shall also be published in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of every notice or proclamation issued sub-section (1) shall be served on the defaulter.`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (37495)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `Sale to be by auction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37495&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `All sales of property, movable or immovable, under this Chapter shall be`
  line `by public auction held in accordance with such rules as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (37496)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Prohibition to bid at auction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37496&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `No officer having any duty to perform in connection with any`
  line `such sale and no person employed by or subordinate to such officer shall, either directly or indirectly, bid`
  line `or acquire any property except on behalf of the Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (37497)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `Sale of perishables.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37497&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `Perishable articles shall be sold by auction with the least possible delay`
  line `and such shall be finally concluded by the office conducting the sale.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (37498)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `Sale not to be excessive.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37498&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `Every sale of property, movable or immovable, under the provisions`
  line `of this Chapter shall, as far as may be practicable, be proportionate to the amount of the arrear of land`
  line `revenue to be recovered together with the interest thereon and the expenses of attachment and sale.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (37499)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `Deposit by purchaser of immovable property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37499&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `In all cases of immovable property, the party`
  line `who is declared to be the purchaser shall be required to deposit immediately 25 per cent. of the amount of`
  line `his bid, and the balance within fifteen days of the date of sale.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (37500)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title `Failure to make deposit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37500&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `(1) In default of the payment of deposit referred to in section 71, the`
  line `property shall be put up for re-sale and the expenses incurred in connection with the first sale shall be`
  line `borne by the defaulting bidder.`
  line
  line `(2) In default of payment of the balance of the bid amount within the period prescribed in section 71,`
  line `the deposit after defraying therefrom the expenses of the sale shall be forfeited to the Government and the`
  line `property shall be re-sold.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the proceeds of the re-sale are less than the price bid by such defaulting purchaser, the`
  line `difference shall also be recoverable from him in the same manner as an arrear of land revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (37501)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title `Setting aside sale.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37501&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `Where immovable property has been sold under this Chapter, the defaulter,`
  line `or any person owning such property or holding an interest therein, may, at any time, within thirty days of`
  line `the date of sale or within such further period not exceeding thirty days as the deputy commissioner may`
  line `for sufficient cause allow, apply in the prescribed manner to the deputy commissioner to have the sale set`
  line aside--
  line
  line `(a) on the ground of some material irregularity or mistake or fraud resulting in substantial loss or`
  line `injury to him, or`
  line
  line `(b) on his depositing in the deputy commissioner's office the amount of the arrear specified in the`
  line `proclamation of sale, the cost of the sale and for payment to the purchaser a sum equal to five per`
  line `cent. of the purchase money.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (37502)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title `Confirmation of sale.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37502&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `If, on the expiration of 30 days from the date of sale of any immovable`
  line `property or of the further period, if any, allowed under section 73, no application has been made for`
  line `setting aside the sale, or if any such application has been made and rejected, the deputy commissioner`
  line `shall make an order confirming the sale unless, for reasons to be recorded, the deputy commissioner sets`
  line `aside the sale notwithstanding that no application therefor has been made.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (37503)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title Refunds.
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37503&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `(1) The deputy commissioner shall order the refund and payment to the`
  line `purchaser, of--`
  line
  line `(a) the amounts deposited by him under section 71; and`
  line
  line `(b) the sum equal to 5 per cent. of the purchase money deposited under clause (b) of section 73;`
  line
  line `if the sale is not confirmed or is set aside.`
  line
  line `(2) The deputy commissioner shall order the refund and payment of all monies deposited under`
  line `clause (b) of section 73 to the person who made the deposit, if the sale is confirmed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the deputy commissioner may set off the whole or any part of any such monies against`
  line `any arrear of land revenue or any other amount recoverable as an arrear of land revenue, which may be`
  line `outstanding against the person who made the deposit.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (37504)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 76
  title `Certificate of purchase.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37504&sectionno=76&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `When a sale held under this Chapter is confirmed, the deputy`
  line `commissioner shall put the person declared to be the purchaser in possession of the property and shall`
  line `grant him a certificate in the prescribed form to the effect that he has purchased the property specified`
  line `therein, and such certificate shall be deemed to be a valid transfer of such property.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (37505)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 77
  title `Application of proceeds of sale.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37505&sectionno=77&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `The proceeds of the sale of any property under this Chapter`
  line `shall be applied in defraying the expenses of the sale which shall be determined in the prescribed manner`
  line `and the balance shall be applied to the payment of the arrears on account of which the sale was held and`
  line `the surplus, if any, shall be paid to the person whose property has been sold.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (37506)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 78
  title `Liability of certified purchaser.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37506&sectionno=78&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `The person who has purchased any land and to whom a`
  line `certificate of purchase has been granted shall not be liable for the land revenue in respect of the land for`
  line `any period prior to the date of the sale.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (37507)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 79
  title `Precautionary measures in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37507&sectionno=79&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `When the crop of any land or any portion of the`
  line `same is sold, mortgaged or otherwise disposed of, the deputy commissioner may, if he thinks it necessary,`
  line `prevent its being removed from the land until the demand for the current year in respect of the said land is`
  line `paid, whether the date fixed for the payment of the same has arrived or not.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (37508)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 80
  title `Recovery of other public demands.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37508&sectionno=80&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `The following monies may be recovered under this Act in`
  line `the same manner as an arrear of land revenue, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) rent, fees and royalties due to the Government for use or occupation of land or water or any`
  line `product of land;`
  line
  line `(b) all monies falling due to the Government under any grant, lease or contract which provides`
  line `that they shall be recoverable as an arrear of land revenue;`
  line
  line `(c) all sums declared by this Act or any other law for the time being in force to be recoverable as`
  line `an arrear of land revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (37509)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 81
  title `Revenue officers to be courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37509&sectionno=81&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `(1) A revenue officer, while exercising power under this Act or`
  line `any other law for the time being in force to inquire into or to decide any question arising for`
  line `determination between the Government and any person or between parties to any proceedings, shall be a`
  line `revenue court.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in this Act shall be deemed to limit or otherwise affect the inherent power of the revenue`
  line `court to make such orders as may be necessary for the ends of justice or to prevent the abuse of the`
  line `process of the revenue court.`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (37510)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 82
  title `Place of hearing.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37510&sectionno=82&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `Except for reasons to be recorded in writing, no revenue officer shall inquire`
  line `into or hear any case at any place outside the local limits of his jurisdiction:`
  line
  line `Provided that a sub-divisional officer may inquire into or hear any case at the headquarters of the`
  line `district to which he is appointed.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (37511)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 83
  title `Power to enter upon and survey land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37511&sectionno=83&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `All revenue officers and persons acting under their`
  line `orders may, enter upon and survey any land and demarcate boundaries and do all other acts necessary for`
  line `the purpose of discharging their duties under this Act or any other law for the time being in force and in`
  line `so doing, shall cause no more damage than the circumstances of the case may require.`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (37512)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 84
  title `Power to transfer cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37512&sectionno=84&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Administrator may transfer any case or class of cases arising`
  line `under this Act or any other law for the time being in force from any revenue officer to any other revenue`
  line `officer competent to deal with it.`
  line
  line `(2) The deputy commissioner or a sub-divisional officer may transfer any case or class of cases`
  line `arising under this Act or any other law for the time being in force for inquiry or decision from his own file`
  line `or from the file of any revenue officer subordinate to him to the file of any other revenue officer`
  line `subordinate to him competent to deal with such case or class of cases.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (37513)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 85
  title `Power to take evidence, summon witnesses, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37513&sectionno=85&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every revenue officer not lower in rank`
  line `than a sub-deputy collector acting as a revenue court shall have power to take evidence and to summon`
  line `any person whose attendance he considers necessary, either as a party or as a witness or to produce any`
  line `document, for the purpose of any inquiry which such officer is legally empowered to make; and all`
  line `persons so summoned shall be bound to attend either in person or by an authorised agent as such officer`
  line `may direct, and to produce such documents as may be required.`
  line
  line `(2) Every summons shall be in writing, signed and sealed by the officer issuing it and shall be in such`
  line `form and be served in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (37514)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 86
  title `Compelling attendance of witnesses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37514&sectionno=86&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `If any person on whom a summons to attend as witness`
  line `or to produce any document has been served fails to comply with the summons, the officer by whom the`
  line `summons has been issued under section 85 may--`
  line
  line `(a) issue a bailable warrant of arrest;`
  line
  line `(b) order him to furnish security for appearance; or`
  line
  line `(c) impose upon him a fine not exceeding rupees twenty.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (37515)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 87
  title `Hearing in absence of party.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37515&sectionno=87&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, on the date fixed for hearing a case or proceeding, a`
  line `revenue officer finds that a summons or notice was not served on any party due to the failure of the`
  line `opposite party to pay the requisite process fees for such service, the case or proceeding may be dismissed`
  line `for default of payment of such process fees.`
  line
  line `(2) If any party to a case or proceeding before a revenue officer does not appear on the date fixed for`
  line `hearing, the case or proceeding may be heard and determined in his absence or may be dismissed for`
  line default.
  line
  line `(3) The party against whom any order is passed under sub-section (1) or (2) may apply, within thirty`
  line `days from the date of such order, to have it set aside on the ground that he was prevented by sufficient`
  line `cause from paying the requisite process fees or from appearing at the hearing; and the revenue officer`
  line `may, after notice to the opposite party and after making such inquiry as he considers necessary, set aside`
  line `the order passed.`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (37516)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 88
  title `Adjournment of hearing.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37516&sectionno=88&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `(1) A revenue officer may, from time to time, for reasons to be`
  line `recorded, adjourn the hearing of a case or proceeding before him.`
  line
  line `(2) The date and place of an adjourned hearing shall be intimated at the time of the adjournment to`
  line `such of the parties and witnesses as are present.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (37517)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 89
  title `Power to order payment of costs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37517&sectionno=89&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `A revenue officer may direct the parties to pay the cost`
  line `incurred in any case before him and also apportion the cost among the parties in such manner and to such`
  line `extent as he may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (37518)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 90
  title `Use of force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37518&sectionno=90&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `Where any order is passed under the provisions of this Act directing any person`
  line `to deliver possession of land or directing the eviction of any person from land, such order shall be`
  line `executed by the competent authority in such manner as may be prescribed and it shall be lawful for such`
  line `authority, in accordance with rules to be prescribed, to take such steps and use or cause to be used such`
  line `force as may be reasonably necessary for securing compliance with the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (37519)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 91
  title `Appearances before and applications to revenue officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37519&sectionno=91&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `All appearances before,`
  line `applications to and acts to be done before, any revenue officer under this Act or any other law for the time`
  line `being in force may be made or done by the parties themselves or by their authorised agents or by any`
  line `legal practitioner:`
  line
  line `Provided that any such appearance shall, if the revenue officer so directs, be made by the party in`
  line person.
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (37520)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 92
  title `Correction of error or omission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37520&sectionno=92&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line `Any revenue officer by whom an order was passed in a case`
  line `or proceeding may, either on his own motion or on the application of a party, correct any error or`
  line `omission not affecting a material part of the case or proceeding, after such notice to the parties as he may`
  line `consider necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (37521)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 93
  title Appeals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37521&sectionno=93&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise expressly provided, an appeal shall lie from every original order`
  line `passed under this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) if such an order is passed by an officer subordinate to the sub-divisional officer, to the`
  line `sub-divisional officer;`
  line
  line `(b) if such an order is passed by the sub-divisional officer, to the deputy commissioner;`
  line
  line `(c) if such an order is passed by the deputy commissioner, to the Administrator;`
  line
  line `(d) if such an order is passed by an assistant survey and settlement officer, to the survey and`
  line `settlement officer or to a revenue officer notified by the Administrator in the Official Gazette to be`
  line `the appellate authority; and`
  line
  line `(e) if such an order is passed by a survey and settlement officer, to the director of settlement and`
  line `land records or to a revenue officer notified by the Administrator in the Official Gazette to be the`
  line `appellate authority.`
  line
  line `(2) A second appeal shall lie against any order passed in first appeal,--`
  line
  line `(a) if such an order is passed under clause (a) of sub-section (1), to the deputy commissioner;`
  line
  line `(b) if such an order is passed under clause (b) of sub-section (1), to the Administrator;`
  line
  line `(c) if such an order is passed under clause (d) of sub-section (1), to the director of settlement and`
  line `land records or to a revenue officer notified by the Administrator in the Official Gazette to be the`
  line `second appellate authority; and`
  line
  line `(d) if such an order is passed under clause (e) of sub-section (1), to the Administrator.`
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (37522)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 94
  title `Limitation of appeals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37522&sectionno=94&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `(1) No appeal shall lie,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of first appeal, after the expiry of thirty days from the date of the order appealed`
  line `against; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a second appeal, after the expiry of sixty days from the date of the order`
  line `appealed against.`
  line
  line `(2) In computing the above periods, the time required to obtain copies of the order appealed against`
  line `shall be excluded.`
obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (37523)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 95
  title Revision.
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37523&sectionno=95&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `The Administrator or the deputy commissioner may, at any time, either on his own`
  line `motion or on the application of any party, call for the records of any proceedings before any revenue`
  line `officer subordinate to him for the purpose of satisfying himself as to the legality or the propriety of any`
  line `order passed by such revenue officer, and may pass such order in reference thereto as he thinks fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that he shall not vary or reverse any order affecting any right between private persons`
  line `without having given to the parties interested notice to appear and be heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (37524)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 96
  title `Review of orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37524&sectionno=96&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `A revenue officer may, either on his own motion or on the application of any`
  line `party interested, review any order passed by himself or by any of his predecessors-in-office and pass such`
  line `order in reference thereto as he thinks fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that a revenue officer subordinate to the deputy commissioner shall, before reviewing any`
  line `order under this section, obtain the permission of the deputy commissioner and the deputy commissioner`
  line `shall, before reviewing an order passed by any of his predecessors-in-officer, obtain the permission of the`
  line Administrator.
  line
  line `(2) No order affecting any question of right between private persons shall be reviewed except on the`
  line `application of a party to the proceedings or except after notice to the other party, and no application for`
  line `review of such order shall be entertained unless it is made within ninety days from the date of the order.`
  line
  line `(3) No order shall be reviewed except on the following grounds, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) discovery of new and important matter of evidence; or`
  line
  line `(ii) some mistake or error apparent on the face of the record; or`
  line
  line `(iii) any other sufficient reason.`
  line
  line `(4) For the purposes of this section, the deputy commissioner shall be deemed to be the`
  line `successor-in-office of any revenue officer who has left the district or who has ceased to exercise powers`
  line `as a revenue officer and to whom there is no successor in the district.`
  line
  line `(5) An order which has been dealt with in appeal or on revision shall not be reviewed by any officer`
  line `subordinate to the appellate or revisional authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_97:
  sectionId (37525)
  sectionNo (97)
  orderNo 97
  title `Stay of execution of orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_97_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37525&sectionno=97&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_97_content:
  string
  line `(1) A revenue officer who has passed any order or his`
  line `successor-in-office may, at any time before the expiry of the period prescribed for appeal, direct the stay`
  line `of execution of such order for such period as he thinks fit provided that no appeal has been filed.`
  line
  line `(2) Any authority before whom a case is pending in appeal or revision may direct the stay of`
  line `execution of the order appealed from or under revision for such period as it may think fit.`
  line
  line `(3) The revenue officer or other authority directing such stay of execution of any order may impose`
  line `such condition, or order such security to be furnished, as he or it may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_98:
  sectionId (37526)
  sectionNo (98)
  orderNo 98
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_98_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37526&sectionno=98&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_98_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Administrator may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make`
  line `rules for carrying out the purposes of this Part.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner of appointment of revenue officers, survey officers and settlement officers, and`
  line `other village officers and servants, their powers and duties, the official seals, if any, to be used by`
  line `them and the size and description of the seals;`
  line
  line `(b) the deputy commissioners powers of superintendence and control over other officers;`
  line
  line `(c) the officers who should hear and decide disputes regarding rights in or over any property`
  line `claimed by or against the Government and the procedure to be followed by them;`
  line
  line `(d) the disposal of Government lands by assignment or grant to individuals or to public purposes`
  line `and the terms and conditions subject to which such assignments or grants may be made;`
  line
  line `(e) the preservation and disposal of trees, brush wood jungle and other natural products on`
  line `Government land and the recovery of the value of trees or other natural product unauthorisedly`
  line `appropriated by persons;`
  line
  line `(f) the procedure for summary eviction of trespassers on Government land;`
  line
  line `(g) the alteration and revision of the land revenue in cases of alluvion or diluvion or of diversion`
  line `of land for purposes other than agriculture;`
  line
  line `(h) the grant of permission to use agricultural land for non-agricultural purposes;`
  line
  line `(i) the determination of additional rates for use of water;`
  line
  line `(j) the circumstances in which remission or suspension of revenue may be made and the rate of`
  line `such remission or suspension;`
  line
  line `(k) the form of receipt for payment of land revenue;`
  line
  line `(l) the conduct of surveys and settlements of land revenue;`
  line
  line `(m) the manner of estimating the cost of cultivation and other expenses in relation to the inquiry`
  line `into profits of agriculture;`
  line
  line `(n) the division of survey numbers into sub-divisions and the assessment of sub-divisions;`
  line
  line `(o) the statistical, fiscal and other records and registers to be prepared and maintained under this`
  line Part;
  line
  line `(p) the manner in which the costs and expenses incidental to revenue survey or the construction,`
  line `repair and maintenance of boundary marks shall be determined and appointed between persons who`
  line `are liable to bear the same;`
  line
  line `(q) the fixing, construction, laying out, maintenance and repair of boundary marks, and the`
  line `settlement of disputes relating thereto;`
  line
  line `(r) the division of areas into units for determining the revenue-rates and the preparation of the`
  line `table of revenue-rates;`
  line
  line `(s) the preparation and the preliminary and final publication of the record of rights and the table`
  line `of revenue-rates;`
  line
  line `(t) the hearing and disposal of objections to any entry or omission in the table of revenue-rates,`
  line `the record of rights, and the register of mutations;`
  line
  line `(u) the manner and extent of alteration or revision of revenue-rates during the term of settlement;`
  line
  line `(v) the correction of bona fide errors and mistakes in the revenue records, registers and maps`
  line `prepared under this Part;`
  line
  line `(w) the manner in which the average yield of crops of land shall be ascertained;`
  line
  line `(x) the manner of holding inquiries by revenue officers under this Part;`
  line
  line `(y) the application of the provisions of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), to cases`
  line `and proceedings before a revenue court;`
  line
  line `(z) the form of summons and other processes, notices, orders and proclamations to be issued or`
  line `made by revenue officers and the manner of their service;`
  line
  line `(aa) the procedure for the attachment and sale of property and the confirmation and the setting`
  line `aside of sales of immovable property under Chapter VII;`
  line
  line `(bb) the manner of publication of notices and proclamations of attachment and sale of property;`
  line
  line `(cc) the manner in which the cost and expenses incidental to the attachment and sale of property`
  line `shall be determined;`
  line
  line `(dd) the manner of payment of deposit and of the purchases money of property sold for arrears of`
  line `land revenue;`
  line
  line `(ee) the circumstances in which precautionary measures for securing the land revenue under`
  line `section 79 may be taken;`
  line
  line `(ff) the procedure for the transfer of cases from one revenue officer to another;`
  line
  line `(gg) the manner of preferring appeals or applications for revision or review, the documents to`
  line `accompany the memorandum of appeal or such application and the fee, if any, liable therefor;`
  line
  line `(hh) the grant of certified copies and the payment of fees for inspection and grant of certified`
  line `copies of revenue records and registers;`
  line
  line `(ii) the mode of execution of any orders directing any person to deliver possession of land or to be`
  line `evicted from land, including the use of force for securing compliance with such order;`
  line
  line `(jj) any other matter that is to be or may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_99:
  sectionId (37527)
  sectionNo (99)
  orderNo 99
  title `Accrual of rights of landowners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37527&sectionno=99&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person who, at the commencement of this Act,`
  line `holds any land from the Government for agricultural purposes, whether as a settlement-holder or as a`
  line `pattadar and his successors-in-interest shall, subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), become the`
  line `owner thereof as and from such commencement.`
  line
  line `(2) No rights shall accrue under sub-section (1) in respect of lands which--`
  line
  line `(i) are a part of the bed of a river, a nallah, a stream or a public tank, or`
  line
  line `(ii) have been acquired by the Government for any purpose according to the provisions of any law`
  line `in force for the time being relating to acquisition of land, or`
  line
  line `(iii) have been used at any time during the five years immediately preceding the commencement`
  line `of this Act for any public, community or village purpose, or`
  line
  line `(iv) are declared by the Administrator by notification in the Official Gazette as reserved or`
  line `required for any public, community or village purpose.`
  line
  line `(3) Objections to the accrual of rights under sub-section (1) may be filed before the competent`
  line `authority within such time and in such form and manner as may be prescribed by any person who has`
  line `interest or claims to have an interest in the land either in his individual capacity or as a member of the`
  line `village or community.`
  line
  line `(4) Should any objection be made under sub-section (3), the competent authority shall inquire into the`
  line `objection in such manner as may be prescribed and decide the same.`
  line
  line `(5) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the decision of the competent authority shall be final.`
  line
  line `(6) Every person who, at the commencement of this Act, holds land from the Government for a`
  line `purpose other than agriculture shall, subject to sub-section (2), be entitled to the settlement of that land on`
  line `such terms and conditions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(7) Nothing in this section shall entitle any person to the sub-soil rights in respect of the land, of`
  line `which he has become the landowner under sub-section (1), of which has been settled with him under`
  line `sub-section (6).`
obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_100:
  sectionId (37528)
  sectionNo (100)
  orderNo 100
  title `Rights of landowners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_100_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37528&sectionno=100&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_100_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person who has become a landowner under sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 99 shall--`
  line
  line `(a) have permanent, heritable and transferable rights in the land;`
  line
  line `(b) be entitled by himself, his servants, tenants, agents or other representatives to erect farm`
  line `buildings, construct wells or tanks or make any other improvements thereon for the better cultivation`
  line `of the land or its convenient use;`
  line
  line `(c) be entitled to plant trees on the land, to enjoy the products thereof and to fell, utilise or dispose`
  line `of the timber of any trees on the land.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall entitle a landowner to use his land to the detriment of any`
  line `adjoining land which is not his or in contravention of the provisions of any other law for the time being in`
  line `force applicable to such land.`
obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_101:
  sectionId (37529)
  sectionNo (101)
  orderNo 101
  title `Reservation of land for personal cultivation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37529&sectionno=101&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every landowner who, at the`
  line `commencement of this Act, owns land in excess of a basic holding shall be entitled to apply to the`
  line `competent authority for the reservation for his personal cultivation of any parcel or parcels of his land`
  line `leased to tenants.`
  line
  line `(2) Every application under sub-section (1) shall be in the prescribed form and shall be made in the`
  line `prescribed manner within a period of one year from such commencement.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In the case of a person under disability, the application shall be made by his guardian`
  line `or his authorised agent, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_102:
  sectionId (37530)
  sectionNo (102)
  orderNo 102
  title `Procedure for reservation of land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_102_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37530&sectionno=102&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line `(1) On receipt of an application made under section 101,`
  line `the competent authority shall issue notice together with a copy of the application to each of the tenants`
  line `holding land from the applicant requiring the tenant to submit his objections, if any, within a period of`
  line `ninety days from the date of service of such notice or within such further period as the competent`
  line `authority may allow.`
  line
  line `(2) A tenant on whom a notice has been served under sub-section (1) shall furnish to the competent`
  line `authority within the period specified details of lands owned by him or held as tenant of any other`
  line `landowner and of lands which he selects for retention by him.`
  line
  line `(3) The competent authority shall, after considering the objections and the details, if any, furnished by`
  line `the tenants and after making such inquiry as it may consider necessary, determine the land or lands not`
  line `exceeding the permissible limit, which in its opinion having regard to all the circumstances of the case`
  line `may be reserved for personal cultivation of the landowner and the lands which each of his tenants may be`
  line `allowed to retain.`
obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_103:
  sectionId (37531)
  sectionNo (103)
  orderNo 103
  title `“Permissible limit” defined.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_103_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37531&sectionno=103&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_103_content:
  string
  line `(1) In section 102, "permissible limit" means an area of land`
  line `which a landowner may resume from tenants for personal cultivation, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a person under disability, 25 acres;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of any other person who--`
  line
  line `(i) owns a basic holding or less, the entire area owned by him;`
  line
  line `(ii) owns more than a basic holding but not exceeding a family holding, one-half of the area`
  line `leased to tenants or the area by which the land under his personal cultivation falls short of a basic`
  line `holding, whichever is greater;`
  line
  line `(iii) owns more than a family holding--`
  line
  line `(1) if he has no land, or any land which is less than a family holding under his personal`
  line `cultivation, one-half of the area leased to the tenant but not exceeding the area by which land`
  line `under his personal cultivation falls short of a family holding, provided that the tenant is left`
  line `with not less than a basic holding and provided further that a landowner shall in any case be`
  line `entitled to resume an area by which land under his personal cultivation falls short of a basic`
  line `holding; and`
  line
  line `(2) if he has family holding or more under his personal cultivation, the area leased to any`
  line `tenant in excess of a family holding but not exceeding the area by which land in his personal`
  line `cultivation falls short of 25 acres.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of determining the permissible limit of a landowner under this`
  line `sub-section, any no-resumable land which he may hold as a tenant shall also be taken into account.`
  line
  line `(2) Any transfer of land made on or after the 6th day of March, 1956, shall be disregarded in`
  line `computing the permissible limit.`
obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_104:
  sectionId (37532)
  sectionNo (104)
  orderNo 104
  title `Land deemed to be reserved for personal cultivation in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_104_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37532&sectionno=104&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_104_content:
  string
  line `In the case of a`
  line `person who, at the commencement of this Act, does not own land in excess of a basic holding, all lands`
  line `owned by him and held by tenants shall be deemed to have been reserved for his personal cultivation.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--Any transfer of land made on or after the 6th day of March, 1956, shall be disregarded`
  line `in determining the extent of land owned by a person at the commencement of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_105:
  sectionId (37533)
  sectionNo (105)
  orderNo 105
  title `Non-resumable land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_105_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37533&sectionno=105&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_105_content:
  string
  line `The competent authority shall declare every land which, under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 102, a tenant is allowed to retain to be the non-resumable land of the tenant.`
obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_106:
  sectionId (37534)
  sectionNo (106)
  orderNo 106
  title `Right to lease.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_106_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37534&sectionno=106&orderno=106&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_106_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, a landowner may lease out his land to`
  line `another person on such rent not exceeding the maximum rent referred to in section 112 as may be agreed`
  line `upon between him and such person.`
  line
  line `(2) Every lease of land made after the commencement of this Act shall be for a period of five years`
  line `and at the end of the said period, and thereafter at the end of each period of five years, the tenancy shall,`
  line `subject to the provisions of sub-section (3) be deemed to be renewed for a further period of five years on`
  line `the same terms and conditions, except to the extent that a modification thereof consistent with this Act is`
  line `agreed to by both parties.`
  line
  line `(3) In respect of any lease made after the commencement of this Act, a landowner who is a member`
  line `of the Armed Forces of the Union, on his discharge from service or posting to the reserve, may by giving`
  line `the tenant three months' notice in writing before the expiry of any year, and any other landowner may by`
  line `giving the tenant one year's notice in writing before the expiry of any term of five years, terminate the`
  line `tenancy if the landowner requires the land bona fide for personal cultivation by him.`
obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_107:
  sectionId (37535)
  sectionNo (107)
  orderNo 107
  title `Land left uncultivated.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_107_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37535&sectionno=107&orderno=107&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_107_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the deputy commissioner is satisfied that any land has`
  line `remained uncultivated for a period not less than two consecutive years otherwise than in accordance with`
  line `rules made in this behalf under this Act, and that it is necessary for the purpose of ensuring the full and`
  line `efficient use of the land for agriculture to do so, he may after making such inquiry as may be prescribed`
  line `lease out the land in accordance with the rules made under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Any lease made under sub-section (1) shall be deemed to be lease made by the landowner under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 106.`
obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_108:
  sectionId (37536)
  sectionNo (108)
  orderNo 108
  title Relinquishment.
  content obj_root_law_sections_108_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37536&sectionno=108&orderno=108&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_108_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to any rules that may be made under this Act, a landowner may`
  line `relinquish his rights in respect of any land in his possession in favour of Government by giving a notice in`
  line `writing to the competent authority in such form and manner as may be prescribed, not less than three`
  line `months before the close of any year and thereupon, he shall cease to be a landowner in respect of that land`
  line `from the year next following the date of notice:`
  line
  line `Provided that relinquishment of only a part of a holding or of a holding which, or part of which, is`
  line `subject to an encumbrance or a charge, shall not be valid.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person relinquishes his rights to a land under sub-section (1), the way to which lies through`
  line `other land retained by him, any future holder of the land relinquished shall be entitled to a right of way`
  line `through the land retained.`
obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_109:
  sectionId (37537)
  sectionNo (109)
  orderNo 109
  title `Interest of tenants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_109_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37537&sectionno=109&orderno=109&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_109_content:
  string
  line `(1) The interest of a tenant in any land held by him as such shall be`
  line `heritable but, save as otherwise provided in this Act, shall not be transferable.`
  line
  line `(2) No tenant shall be evicted from his land except as provided in this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_110:
  sectionId (37538)
  sectionNo (110)
  orderNo 110
  title `Right to create a mortgage or charge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_110_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37538&sectionno=110&orderno=110&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_110_content:
  string
  line `It shall be lawful for a tenant to create a simple`
  line `mortgage or create a charge on his interest in the land leased to him in favour of the Government or a`
  line `co-operative society in consideration of any loan advanced to him by the Government or such society; and`
  line `in the event of his making default in the repayment of such loan in accordance with its terms, it shall be`
  line `lawful for the Government or the society, as the case may be, to cause his interest in the land to be`
  line `attached and sold and the proceeds applied in payment of such loan.`
obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_111:
  sectionId (37539)
  sectionNo (111)
  orderNo 111
  title `Right to make improvements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_111_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37539&sectionno=111&orderno=111&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_111_content:
  string
  line `A tenant may, with the permission in writing of the landowner,`
  line `or if permission is refused without sufficient reason or not given within two months, after obtaining the`
  line `order of the competent authority in the prescribed manner, make at his own expense any improvement to`
  line `the land held by him, but shall not become liable to pay a higher rate of rent on account of any increase of`
  line `production or of any change in the nature of the crop raised, as a consequence of such improvement.`
obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_112:
  sectionId (37540)
  sectionNo (112)
  orderNo 112
  title `Maximum rent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_112_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37540&sectionno=112&orderno=112&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_112_content:
  string
  line `The rent payable by a tenant in respect of any land held by him shall not`
  line exceed,--
  line
  line `(a) where the rent is payable in kind as a share of the produce, one-fourth of the produce of such`
  line `land or its value estimated in the prescribed manner if plough cattle for the cultivation of such land is`
  line `supplied by the landowner and one-fifth of such produce or its value as so estimated the plough cattle`
  line `is not supplied by the landowner;`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, four times the land revenue payable in respect of the land.`
obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_113:
  sectionId (37541)
  sectionNo (113)
  orderNo 113
  title `Payment of rent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_113_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37541&sectionno=113&orderno=113&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_113_content:
  string
  line `(1) The rent payable by a tenant shall, subject to the provisions of`
  line `section 112, be the rent agreed upon between him and the landowner or where there is no such agreement,`
  line `the reasonable rent.`
  line
  line `(2) The rent shall be paid at such times and in such manner as may have been agreed upon or in the`
  line `absence of such agreement, as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_114:
  sectionId (37542)
  sectionNo (114)
  orderNo 114
  title `Reasonable rent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_114_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37542&sectionno=114&orderno=114&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_114_content:
  string
  line `(1) The competent authority may, on application made to it in this behalf by`
  line `the landowner or the tenant, determine the reasonable rent for any land.`
  line
  line `(2) The form of application under sub-section (1) and the procedure to be followed by the competent`
  line `authority shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) In determining the reasonable rent, the competent authority shall have regard to--`
  line
  line `(a) the rental value of lands used for similar purposes in the locality;`
  line
  line `(b) the profits of agriculture of similar lands in the locality;`
  line
  line `(c) the price of crops and commodities in the locality;`
  line
  line `(d) the improvements, if any, made to the land by the landowner or the tenant;`
  line
  line `(e) the land revenue payable in respect of the land; and`
  line
  line `(f) any other factor which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the reasonable rent for any land has been determined under this section, it shall not be`
  line `altered for a period of five years except on any of the following grounds, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) that the quality of the land has deteriorated by flood or other natural causes;`
  line
  line `(b) that there has been an increase in the produce of the land on account of improvements made to`
  line `it at the expense of the landowner;`
  line
  line `(c) that the land has been partially or wholly rendered unfit for cultivation.`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing in sub-sections (1) to (4) shall affect the right of the Government to make an order`
  line `directing the determination of the reasonable rent of lands in any specified area.`
obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_115:
  sectionId (37543)
  sectionNo (115)
  orderNo 115
  title `Commutation of rent payable in kind.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_115_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37543&sectionno=115&orderno=115&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_115_content:
  string
  line `(1) In any case in which rent is payable in kind, the`
  line `landowner or the tenant may apply in writing to the competent authority in the prescribed form and`
  line `manner, for commuting the rent into money rent.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of such application, the competent authority shall, after giving notice to the other party,`
  line `determine the money rent payable for the land in accordance with the following provisions but not`
  line `exceeding the maximum rent specified in section 112.`
  line
  line `(3) In determining the money rent, regard shall be had to--`
  line
  line `(a) the average money rent payable by tenants for land of similar description and with similar`
  line `advantages in the vicinity;`
  line
  line `(b) the average value of the rent actually received by the landowner during the three years`
  line `preceding the date of application;`
  line
  line `(c) the average prices of crops and commodities in the locality during the three years preceding`
  line `the date of application;`
  line
  line `(d) the improvements, if any, made to the land by the landowner or the tenant; and`
  line
  line `(e) any other factor which may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_116:
  sectionId (37544)
  sectionNo (116)
  orderNo 116
  title `Receipt for payment of rent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37544&sectionno=116&orderno=116&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_116_content:
  string
  line `Every landowner shall give or cause to be given a receipt for the`
  line `rent received by him or on his behalf in such form as may be prescribed duly signed by him or his`
  line `authorised agent.`
obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_117:
  sectionId (37545)
  sectionNo (117)
  orderNo 117
  title `Refund of rent recovered in excess.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_117_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37545&sectionno=117&orderno=117&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_117_content:
  string
  line `If any landowner recovers from a tenant rent in excess of`
  line `the amount due under this Act, he shall forthwith refund the excess amount so recovered and shall also be`
  line `liable to punishment as provided in this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_118:
  sectionId (37546)
  sectionNo (118)
  orderNo 118
  title `Suspension or remission of rent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_118_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37546&sectionno=118&orderno=118&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_118_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a landowner has obtained from or been granted`
  line `by the Government any relief by way of suspension or remission, whether in whole or in part, of the land`
  line `revenue payable in respect of his land, he shall be bound to give and the tenant concerned shall be entitled`
  line `to receive from the landowner a corresponding or proportionate relief by way of suspension or remission`
  line `of rent payable in respect of such land.`
  line
  line `(2) The nature and extent of the relief which a landowner is bound to give and which the tenant is`
  line `entitled to receive under sub-section (1) shall be determined in accordance with the rules made under this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(3) No suit shall lie and no decree of a civil court shall be executed for the recovery by a landowner of`
  line `any rent the payment of which has been remitted, or during the period for which the payment of such rent`
  line `has been suspended, under this section.`
  line
  line `(4) The period during which the payment of rent is suspended under this section shall be excluded in`
  line `computing the period of limitation prescribed for any suit or proceeding for the recovery of such rent.`
  line
  line `(5) If any landowner fails to suspended or remit the payment of rent as provided in sub-section (1), he`
  line `shall be liable to refund to the tenant the amount recovered by him in contravention of the provisions of`
  line `this section and shall also be liable to punishment as provided in this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_119:
  sectionId (37547)
  sectionNo (119)
  orderNo 119
  title `Eviction of tenant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_119_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37547&sectionno=119&orderno=119&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_119_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall evicted from any land held by him as tenant except`
  line `under the order of the competent authority made on any of the following grounds, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) that the land has been reserved for personal cultivation of the landowner under section 102, or`
  line `is deemed to have been reserved for personal cultivation of the landowner under section 104;`
  line
  line `(b) that a notice has been given to the tenant under sub-section (3) of section 106;`
  line
  line `(c) that the tenant has intentionally and wilfully committed such acts of waste as are calculated to`
  line `impair materially or permanently the value or utility of the land for agricultural purposes;`
  line
  line `(d) that the tenant has failed to pay rent within a period of three months after it falls due:`
  line
  line `Provided that the competent authority may, if it thinks fit, grant further time not exceeding six`
  line `months for payment of the rent;`
  line
  line `(e) that the tenant, not being a person under disability, has after the commencement of this Act,`
  line `sub-let the land without the consent in writing of the landowner.`
  line
  line `(2) No order for eviction of a tenant shall be executed till the standing crops, if any, on the land are`
  line harvested.
  line
  line `(3) Where any order for eviction has been made against a tenant on the ground specified in clause (a)`
  line `of sub-section (1), then, notwithstanding such order, the tenant shall, until he is provided with alternative`
  line `land in accordance with the rules made in this behalf, be entitled to retain possession of--`
  line
  line `(i) the entire land held by him as a tenant, in any case where the area of tenancy together with any`
  line `other land held by him does not exceed 1.25 acres in area; and`
  line
  line `(ii) so much of the land held by him as a tenant as together with any other land held by him does`
  line `not exceed the limit of 1.25 acres in area, in any case where the area of the tenancy together with the`
  line `other land held by him exceeds the said limit:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall apply to a tenanat who holds land under any person`
  line `who is a member of the Armed Forces of the Union.`
  line
  line `(4) Where any land has been reserved for the personal cultivation of a landowner by an order made`
  line `under sub-section (3) of section 102, no suit or application for the eviction of the tenant in respect of such`
  line `land under clause (a) of sub-section (1) shall lie after the expiry of five years from the commencement of`
  line `this Act or one year from the date of the said order, whichever is later:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any such landowner is a person under disability, such suit or application may be`
  line `instituted or made within a period of five years from the date when the disability ceases.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, the disability of a person shall cease--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a widow, if she remarries, on the date of her remarriage or if any person`
  line `succeeds to the widow on her death, on the date of her death;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a minor, on the date of his attaining majority;`
  line
  line `(c) in the case of a woman who is unmarried or who is divorced or judicially separated from her`
  line `husband, on the date of her marriage or remarriage, as the case may be, or in the case of a woman`
  line `whose husband is a person falling under clause (d) or (e), on the date on which the disability of the`
  line `husband ceases;`
  line
  line `(d) in the case of a person who is a member of the Armed Forces of the Union, on the date of his`
  line `discharge from service or of his posting to the reserve;`
  line
  line `(e) in the case of a person suffering from a physical or mental disability, on the date on which the`
  line `disability ceases to exist.`
obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_120:
  sectionId (37548)
  sectionNo (120)
  orderNo 120
  title `Restoration of possession of land to tenant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_120_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37548&sectionno=120&orderno=120&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_120_content:
  string
  line `Where a person who has taken possession of any`
  line `land by evicting tenant therefrom on the ground that the land had been reserved for personal cultivation`
  line `by him fails to cultivate such land personally within one year from the date on which he took possession`
  line `thereof or ceases to cultivate such land personally in any year during a period of four years next`
  line `following, the tenant shall be entitled to be restored to possession of the land from which he was evicted.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this section, land shall not be deemed to be under the personal`
  line `cultivation of a person (not being a person under disability) unless such person or a member of his family`
  line `engages himself in the principal agricultural operations.`
obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_121:
  sectionId (37549)
  sectionNo (121)
  orderNo 121
  title `Certain lands to be non-resumable land of tenant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_121_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37549&sectionno=121&orderno=121&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_121_content:
  string
  line `If a landowner fails to--`
  line
  line `(a) apply for reservation of any land within the period prescribed in section 101, and the land is`
  line `not deemed to have been reserved under section 104, or`
  line
  line `(b) file a suit or application for the eviction of the tenant from any land reserved under`
  line `section 102 within the period prescribed in sub-section (4) of section 119, or`
  line
  line `(c) cultivate or ceases to cultivate the land and the tenant is restored to possession of the land`
  line `under section 120,`
  line
  line `the competent authority may suo motu and shall, on application, after making such inquiry as may be`
  line `prescribed, declare the land to be the non-resumable land of the tenant.`
obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_122:
  sectionId (37550)
  sectionNo (122)
  orderNo 122
  title `Compensation for improvements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_122_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37550&sectionno=122&orderno=122&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_122_content:
  string
  line `(1) A tenant who has made any improvement at his own`
  line `expense on the land leased to him shall, if he is to be evicted under the provisions of this Chapter, be`
  line `entitled to receive compensation before he is so evicted for such improvement as in the opinion of the`
  line `competent authority, is reasonable.`
  line
  line `(2) The compensation payable to a tenant under sub-section (1) shall be determined in accordance`
  line `with the value of such improvements on the date of eviction, and in determining such compensation,`
  line `regard shall be had to the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the amount by which the value of the land has increased by reason of the improvement;`
  line
  line `(b) the condition of the improvement at the date of the determination of the value thereof and the`
  line `probable duration of its effect;`
  line
  line `(c) the labour and capital involved in the making of the improvement; and`
  line
  line `(d) the advantages secured by the tenant in consideration of the improvement made by him.`
  line
  line `(3) In any case in which compensation is payable to a tenant under this section, the competent`
  line `authority may direct that--`
  line
  line `(a) the whole or any part of any loan which the tenant has taken on the security of his interest in`
  line `the land under section 110 and which is outstanding shall be deducted from such compensation and`
  line `paid to the Government or the co-operative society, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(b) any arrear of rent due by the tenant to the landowner and the costs, if any, awarded to the`
  line `landowner shall be adjusted against the compensation.`
obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_123:
  sectionId (37551)
  sectionNo (123)
  orderNo 123
  title `Tenant may remove buildings, works, etc., not deemed improvements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_123_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37551&sectionno=123&orderno=123&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_123_content:
  string
  line `A tenant against`
  line `whom an order of eviction has been passed, shall be entitled to remove within such time as is deemed`
  line `reasonable by the competent authority any work of improvement which can be severed from the land and`
  line `which the tenant desires to remove, or any building or construction or work (which is not an`
  line `improvement) in respect of which the landowner is not willing to pay the compensation.`
obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_124:
  sectionId (37552)
  sectionNo (124)
  orderNo 124
  title `Restoration of possession of land in certain other cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_124_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37552&sectionno=124&orderno=124&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_124_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a tenant of any land has,`
  line `on or after the 6th day of March, 1956, surrendered, or been evicted from, such land, and the surrender or`
  line `eviction could not have taken place if this Act had been in force on the date of such surrender or eviction,`
  line `the competent authority may, suo motu or on application made by the tenant, restore him to possession of`
  line `the land which he surrendered or from which he was evicted unless some other tenant not being a member`
  line `of the landowner's family, had bona fide been admitted to possession of such land.`
  line
  line `(2) The competent authority shall, before making an order under sub-section (1), make such inquiry`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_125:
  sectionId (37553)
  sectionNo (125)
  orderNo 125
  title `Relief against termination of tenancy for act of waste.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_125_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37553&sectionno=125&orderno=125&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_125_content:
  string
  line `Where a tenancy is sought to be`
  line `terminated on the ground that the tenant has materially impaired the value or utility of the land for`
  line `agricultural purposes, if the damage to the land admits of being repaired or if pecuniary compensation`
  line `would afford adequate relief, no proceeding for eviction shall lie against the tenant unless and until the`
  line `landowner has served on the tenant a notice in writing specifying the damage complained of and the`
  line `tenant has failed within a period of one year from the service of such notice to repair the damage or to pay`
  line `compensation therefor.`
obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_126:
  sectionId (37554)
  sectionNo (126)
  orderNo 126
  title `Surrender of land by tenant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_126_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37554&sectionno=126&orderno=126&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_126_content:
  string
  line `(1) After the commencement of this Act, no tenant shall`
  line `surrender any land held by him as such, and no landowner shall enter upon the land surrendered by the`
  line `tenant, without the previous permission in writing of the competent authority.`
  line
  line `(2) Such permission shall be granted if, after making such inquiry as may be prescribed, the`
  line `competent authority is satisfied that the proposed surrender is bona fide and in case the surrender is by a`
  line `person who was holding the land as tenant immediately before the commencement of this Act, the`
  line `permissible limit of the landowner concerned is not exceeded by such surrender; in other cases, the`
  line `permission shall be refused.`
  line
  line `(3) Where permission is refused in any case, and the tenant gives a declaration in writing`
  line `relinquishing his rights in the land, the competent authority shall, in accordance with the rules made in`
  line `this behalf, lease out the land to any other person who shall acquire all the rights of the tenant who`
  line `relinquished his rights.`
obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_127:
  sectionId (37555)
  sectionNo (127)
  orderNo 127
  title `Transfer of ownership of land to tenant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37555&sectionno=127&orderno=127&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_127_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the other provisions of this Act, the`
  line `ownership of any land which is declared to be the non-resumable land of a tenant under section 105, or`
  line `section 121 shall stand transferred from the landowner thereof to the tenant with effect from the date of`
  line `such declaration, and the tenant shall become the owner of such land and be liable to pay land revenue`
  line `therefor:`
  line
  line `Provided that where, on an application made in this behalf by any person at any time before the`
  line `declaration is made under section 105 or under section 121, the competent authority is satisfied that such`
  line `person holds land not exceeding a family holding, whether as a landowner or otherwise, and that his`
  line `income is derived mainly from such land, the competent authority may, by order, provide that the transfer`
  line `of ownership of the land shall take effect on the expiry of a period of five years from the date of such`
  line declaration.
obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_128:
  sectionId (37556)
  sectionNo (128)
  orderNo 128
  title `Compensation to landowner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_128_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37556&sectionno=128&orderno=128&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_128_content:
  string
  line `(1) In respect of every land the ownership of which stands`
  line `transferred to the tenant under section 127, the landowner shall be entitled to compensation which shall`
  line `consist of the aggregate of the following amounts, this is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) an amount equal to thirty times the full land revenue payable for the land or, if the land is held`
  line `revenue-free or at a concessional rate, thirty times the amount of land revenue payable for similar`
  line `lands in the locality;`
  line
  line `(b) the value of trees, if any, planned by the landowner.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--Where any improvement has been made on the land at the expense of the landowner at`
  line `any time subsequent to the last settlement, the land revenue for the purpose of this section shall be the`
  line `land revenue payable for similar lands in the locality.`
  line
  line `(2) The land revenue payable for similar lands in the locality and the value of trees referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) shall be determined in the prescribed manner.`
  line
  line `(3) Every landowner entitled to compensation under this section shall, within a period of six months`
  line `from the date of the declaration referred to in section 127, apply to the competent authority in the`
  line `prescribed manner for determining the compensation.`
obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_129:
  sectionId (37557)
  sectionNo (129)
  orderNo 129
  title `Payment of compensation to landowner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_129_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37557&sectionno=129&orderno=129&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_129_content:
  string
  line `(1) The compensation to which a landowner is`
  line `entitled under section 128 shall be paid to him by the Government in the first instance, and it may be paid`
  line `in cash, in lump sum or in annual instalments not exceeding ten or in the form of bonds which may be`
  line `negotiable or non-negotiable but transferable.`
  line
  line `(2) From the date of the declaration referred to in section 127, the landowner shall be entitled to`
  line `interest at the rate of 2½ per cent. per annum on the compensation or such portion thereof as remains`
  line unpaid.
  line
  line `(3) Any mortgage of, or encumbrance on, the land of which the ownership is transferred to the tenant`
  line `under section 127 shall be a valid charge on the amount of compensation payable to the landowner.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) to (3), where the person entitled to`
  line `compensation under section 128 is a charitable or religious institution, the compensation shall, instead of`
  line `being assessed under that section, be assessed as a perpetual annuity equal to the reasonable rent for the`
  line `land, less the land revenue payable on such land. The amount so assessed shall be paid to such institution`
  line `in the prescribed manner.`
obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_130:
  sectionId (37558)
  sectionNo (130)
  orderNo 130
  title `Tenant to pay compensation amount.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_130_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37558&sectionno=130&orderno=130&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_130_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every tenant to whom ownership of any land has`
  line `been transferred under section 127 shall be liable to pay to the Government in respect of that land`
  line `compensation as determined under section 128.`
  line
  line `(2) The compensation shall be payable in cash, in lump sum or in such number of annual instalments`
  line `not exceeding twenty as may be prescribed. Interest at the rate of 2½ per cent. annum shall be payable on`
  line `the compensation or such portion thereof as remains unpaid.`
  line
  line `(3) The compensation payable under this section shall be a charge on the land.`
  line
  line `(4) The compensation or any instalment thereof shall be recoverable in the same manner as an arrear`
  line `of land revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_131:
  sectionId (37559)
  sectionNo (131)
  orderNo 131
  title `Issue of certificate to tenants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_131_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37559&sectionno=131&orderno=131&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_131_content:
  string
  line `When the compensation or the first instalment of the`
  line `compensation, as the case may be, has been paid by the tenant, the competent authority may suo motu and`
  line `shall, on application made to it in this behalf, issue to the tenant a certificate in the prescribed form`
  line `declaring him to be the owner of the land specified therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_132:
  sectionId (37560)
  sectionNo (132)
  orderNo 132
  title `First option to purchase.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_132_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37560&sectionno=132&orderno=132&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_132_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a landowner at any time intends to sell his land held by a`
  line `tenant, he shall give notice in writing of his intention to such tenant and offer to sell the land to him. In`
  line `case the letter intends to purchase the land, he shall intimate in writing his readiness to do so within two`
  line `months from the date of receipt of such notice.`
  line
  line `(2) If there is any dispute about the reasonable price payable for the land, either the landowner or the`
  line `tenant may apply in writing to the competent authority for determining the reasonable price; and the`
  line `competent authority, after giving notice to the other party and to all other persons interested in the land`
  line `and after making such inquiry as it thinks fit, shall fix the reasonable price of the land which shall be the`
  line `average of the prices obtaining for similar lands in the locality during the ten years immediately preceding`
  line `the date on which the application is made.`
  line
  line `(3) The tenant shall deposit with the competent authority the amount of the price determined under`
  line `sub-section (2) within such period as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) On deposit of the entire amount of the reasonable price, the prescribed authority shall issue a`
  line `certificate in the prescribed form to the tenant declaring him to be the purchaser of the land; the`
  line `competent authority shall also direct that the reasonable price deposited shall be paid to the landowner.`
  line
  line `(5) If the tenant does not exercise the right of purchase in response to the notice given to him by the`
  line `landowner under sub-section (1) or fails to deposit the amount of the price as required by sub-section (3),`
  line `such tenant shall forfeit his right of purchase, and the landowner shall be entitled to sell such land to any`
  line `other person.`
  line
  line `(6) The forfeiture of the right to purchase any land under this section shall not affect the other rights`
  line `of tenant in such land.`
obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_133:
  sectionId (37561)
  sectionNo (133)
  orderNo 133
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_133_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37561&sectionno=133&orderno=133&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_133_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Administrator may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Part.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the form of notices to be issued under this Part and the manner of their service;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner of holding inquiries under this Part;`
  line
  line `(c) the circumstances in which and the period for which land used for agricultural purposes may`
  line `be left uncultivated;`
  line
  line `(d) the conditions subject to which lands may be leased by the deputy commissioner under`
  line `section 107;`
  line
  line `(e) the form of applications to be made under this Part, the authorities to whom they may be made`
  line `and the procedure to be followed by such authorities in disposing of the applications;`
  line
  line `(f) the determination of the value of the produce of land, the profits of agriculture, and the rental`
  line `values of land, for the purposes of this Part;`
  line
  line `(g) the time and manner of payment of rent by the tenant;`
  line
  line `(h) the form of receipt for rent to be given by the landowner;`
  line
  line `(i) the factors to be taken into account in determining reasonable rent for land and in commuting`
  line `rent in kind into money rent;`
  line
  line `(j) the nature and the extent of relief to the tenant in cases of suspension or remission of land`
  line `revenue by the Government;`
  line
  line `(k) the determination of compensation for improvements to tenants who are evicted from land;`
  line
  line `(l) the grant of permission to surrender land;`
  line
  line `(m) the determination of the amount of compensation payable to the landowner in respect of the`
  line `non-resumable lands of tenants;`
  line
  line `(n) the form of certificates to be granted to tenants;`
  line
  line `(o) the determination of the price to be paid by tenant for land in respect of which the first option`
  line `to purchase is exercised;`
  line
  line `(p) any other matter which is to be or may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_134:
  sectionId (37562)
  sectionNo (134)
  orderNo 134
  title Exemption.
  content obj_root_law_sections_134_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37562&sectionno=134&orderno=134&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_134_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Chapter shall not apply to land owned by the Government`
  line `or a local authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_135:
  sectionId (37563)
  sectionNo (135)
  orderNo 135
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_135_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37563&sectionno=135&orderno=135&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_135_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of this Chapter,--`
  line
  line `(a) "ceiling limit", in relation to land, means the limit fixed under section 136;`
  line
  line `(b) "family", in relation to a person, means the person, the wife or husband, as the case may be,`
  line `and the dependent children and grandchildren, of such person;`
  line
  line `(c) "land" does not include land used for non-agricultural purposes.`
obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_136:
  sectionId (37564)
  sectionNo (136)
  orderNo 136
  title `Ceiling on holdings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_136_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37564&sectionno=136&orderno=136&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_136_content:
  string
  line `No person either by himself, or, if he has a family, together with any`
  line `other member of his family (hereinafter referred to as the person representing the family) shall, whether`
  line `as a landowner or as a tenant or as a mortgagee with possession or otherwise, or partly in one capacity`
  line `and partly in another, hold land in excess of twenty-five acres in the aggregate:`
  line
  line `Provided that, where the number of members of the family of such person exceeds five, he may hold`
  line `five additional acres for each member in excess of five, so however as not to exceed fifty acres in the`
  line aggregate.
  line
  line `Explanation.--In the case of a company, an association or any other body of individuals, the ceiling`
  line `limit shall be twenty-five acres.`
obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_137:
  sectionId (37565)
  sectionNo (137)
  orderNo 137
  title `Submission of returns.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_137_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37565&sectionno=137&orderno=137&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_137_content:
  string
  line `Every person representing a family who at the commencement of this`
  line `Act holds, or has at any time during the period between the 15th day of January, 1959 and such`
  line `commencement held, land in excess of the ceiling limit shall submit to the competent authority, in such`
  line `form and within such time as may be prescribed, a return giving the particulars of all land held by him`
  line `and indicating therein the parcels of land, not exceeding the ceiling limit, which he desires to retain:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of joint-holding, all co-sharers may submit the return jointly indicating the`
  line `parcels of land, not exceeding the aggregate of their individual ceiling limits which they desire to retain.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In the case of a person under disability, the return shall be furnished by his guardian or`
  line `authorised agent, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_138:
  sectionId (37566)
  sectionNo (138)
  orderNo 138
  title `Collection of information through other agency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_138_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37566&sectionno=138&orderno=138&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_138_content:
  string
  line `If any person who under section 137 is`
  line `required to submit a return, fails to do so, the competent authority may collect the necessary information`
  line `through such agency as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_139:
  sectionId (37567)
  sectionNo (139)
  orderNo 139
  title `Procedure for determination of excess land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_139_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37567&sectionno=139&orderno=139&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_139_content:
  string
  line `(1) On receipt of any return under section 137`
  line `or information under section 138 or otherwise, the competent authority shall, after giving the persons`
  line `affected an opportunity of being heard, hold an inquiry in such manner as may be prescribed, and having`
  line `regard to the provisions of section 140 and section 141 and of any rules that may be made in this behalf, it`
  line `shall determine--`
  line
  line `(a) the total area of land held by each person representing the family;`
  line
  line `(b) the specific parcels of land which he may retain;`
  line
  line `(c) the land held by him in excess of the ceiling limit;`
  line
  line `(d) whether such excess land is held by him as a landowner or as a tenant or as a mortgage with`
  line possession;
  line
  line `(e) the excess land in respect of which the tenant or the mortgagee with possession may acquire`
  line `the rights of the landowner of the mortgagor, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(f) the excess land which may be restored to a landowner or a mortgagor;`
  line
  line `(g) the excess land which shall vest in the Government; and`
  line
  line `(h) such other matters as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of determining the excess land under this section, any land transferred at any`
  line `time during the period between the 15th day of January, 1959 and the commencement of this Act shall,`
  line `notwithstanding such transfer, be deemed to be held by the transferor.`
  line
  line `(3) The competent authority shall prepare a list in the prescribed form containing the particulars`
  line `determined by it under sub-section (1) and shall cause every such list to be published in the Official`
  line `Gazette and also in such other manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_140:
  sectionId (37568)
  sectionNo (140)
  orderNo 140
  title `Selection of excess land in cases of certain transfers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_140_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37568&sectionno=140&orderno=140&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_140_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any person holding land in`
  line `excess of the ceiling limit at any time during the period between the 15th day of January, 1959, and`
  line `the 9th day of December, 1959, has transferred during such period any part of his land to any other person`
  line `under a registered deed for valuable consideration, the excess land to be determined under section 139`
  line `shall, to the extent possible, be selected out of the land held at the commencement of this Act by the`
  line `transferor in excess of a family holding and no land shall be selected out of the land transferred.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any person holding land in excess of the ceiling limit at any time--`
  line
  line `(a) during the period between the 15th day of January, 1959 and the 9th day of December, 1959,`
  line `has transferred during such period any part of his land to any other person in any manner other than`
  line `under a registered deed for valuable consideration, or`
  line
  line `(b) during the period between the 9th day of December, 1959 and the commencement of this Act`
  line `has transferred during such period any part of his land to any other person in any manner whatsoever,`
  line
  line `the excess land to be determined under section 139 shall be selected out of the lands held at the`
  line `commencement of this Act by the transferor and the transferee in the same proportion as the land held by`
  line `the transferor bears to the land transferred and where no land is held by the transferor, out of the land`
  line transferred.
  line
  line `(3) Where excess land is to be selected out of the lands of more than one transferee, such land shall be`
  line `selected out of the lands held by each of the transferees in the same proportion as the area of the land`
  line `transferred to him bears to the total area of the lands transferred to all the transferees.`
  line
  line `(4) Where any excess land is selected out of the land transferred, the transfer of such land shall be`
  line void.
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything hereinbefore contained, the excess land to be selected shall in no case`
  line `include the homestead land of a person.`
  line
  line `Explanation--For the purpose of this sub-section, "homestead land" means the land on which the`
  line `homestead (whether used by the owner or let out on rent) stands together with any courtyard, compound`
  line `and attached garden, not exceeding one acre in the aggregate.`
obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_141:
  sectionId (37569)
  sectionNo (141)
  orderNo 141
  title `Excess land to vest in Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_141_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37569&sectionno=141&orderno=141&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_141_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any excess land of a landowner is in his actual`
  line `possession, the excess land shall vest in the Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any excess land of a landowner is in the possession of a person holding the same as a`
  line `tenant or as a mortgagee and the excess land together with any other land held by such person exceeds his`
  line `ceiling limit, the land in excess of the ceiling limit shall vest in the Government.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any excess land of a landowner is in the possession of a person holding the same as a`
  line `tenant or as a mortgagee and such person is allowed to retain the excess land or a part thereof as being`
  line `within his ceiling limit, that person shall acquire the rights of the landowner or of the mortgagor, as the`
  line `case may be, in respect of such excess land or part thereof on payment of compensation, if any, as`
  line `hereinafter provided, but if that person refuses to pay such compensation, the excess land or part thereof`
  line `shall vest in the Government.`
  line
  line `(4) Where there is any excess land of a tenant or of a mortgagee with possession, the excess land shall`
  line `vest in the Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in any case where the excess land or any part thereof held by a person as landowner or`
  line `mortgagor together with any other land held by such person does not exceed the ceiling limit, the excess`
  line `land or such part thereof as does not exceed the ceiling limit shall be restored to the possession of that`
  line `person on an application made by him in this behalf to the competent authority within such time as may`
  line `be prescribed and in the case where the possession of such land is restored to the mortgagor, the mortgage`
  line `in respect of such land shall be deemed to be a simple mortgage.`
obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_142:
  sectionId (37570)
  sectionNo (142)
  orderNo 142
  title `Publication of the final list and consequences thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_142_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37570&sectionno=142&orderno=142&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_142_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by an entry`
  line `in the list published under sub-section (3) of section 139 may, within thirty days from the date of`
  line `publication thereof in the Official Gazette, file objections thereto before the deputy commissioner.`
  line
  line `(2) The deputy commissioner or any other officer authorised in this behalf by the Administrator may,`
  line `after considering the objections and after giving the objector or his representatives an opportunity of`
  line `being heard in the matter, approve or modify the list.`
  line
  line `(3) The list as approved or modified under sub-section (2) shall then be published in the Official`
  line `Gazette and also in such other manner as may be prescribed and subject to the provisions of this Act, the`
  line `list shall be final.`
  line
  line `(4) With effect from the date of publication of the list in the Official Gazette under sub-section (3),--`
  line
  line `(a) the excess land shall stand transferred to and vest in the Government free of all`
  line `encumbrances; or`
  line
  line `(b) the possession of the excess land shall stand restored to the landowner or the mortgagor, as the`
  line `case may be; or`
  line
  line `(c) the rights of the landowner or the mortgagor in respect of the excess land shall stand`
  line `transferred to the tenant or the mortgagee, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_143:
  sectionId (37571)
  sectionNo (143)
  orderNo 143
  title Compensation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_143_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37571&sectionno=143&orderno=143&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_143_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any excess land of a landowner vests in the Government, there shall`
  line `be paid by the Government to the landowner compensation, subject to the provisions of sub-section (2),`
  line `of an amount equal to twenty times the net annual income from such land.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of sub-section (1), the net annual income from any land shall be`
  line `deemed to be one-fifth of the value of the average yearly gross produce of the land, calculated in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Where such excess land or any part thereof is in the possession of a tenant, the compensation`
  line `payable under sub-section (1) in respect of the land shall be apportioned between the landowner and the`
  line `tenant in such proportion as may be determined by the competent authority in the prescribed manner,`
  line `having regard to their respective shares in the net income from such land.`
  line
  line `(3) In addition to the compensation payable in respect of any excess land under sub-section (1), there`
  line `shall also be paid compensation in respect of any structure of building constructed on such land and any`
  line `trees planted thereon, and such compensation shall be determined by the competent authority in the`
  line `prescribed manner, having regard to the market value of any structure or building or the value of such`
  line `trees, and such compensation shall be paid to the person who has constructed the structure or building or`
  line `planted the trees.`
  line
  line `(4) Where any excess land in respect of which compensation is payable is subject to any mortgage or`
  line `other encumbrance, the amount due under the mortgage or other encumbrance in respect of such excess`
  line `land, or where a transfer of any excess land is void by virtue of sub-section (4) of section 140, the`
  line `consideration money paid by the transferee in respect of such excess land, shall be a charge on the`
  line `compensation payable in respect of the excess land to the person who has created the mortgage or`
  line `encumbrance or, as the case may be, to the transferor.`
  line
  line `(5) Where a tenant acquires the rights of a landowner in respect of any excess land, the compensation`
  line `payable by him in respect of that land shall be equal to the amount which the landowner would have been`
  line `paid as compensation under sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) if the land had vested in the Government;`
  line `and the amount shall, in the first instance, be paid to the landowner by the Government and shall be`
  line `recovered from the tenant in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(6) Where a mortgagee in possession acquires the rights of the mortgagor in respect of any excess`
  line `land under sub-section (3) of section 141, the compensation payable by the mortgagee in respect of that`
  line `land shall be such sum of money, if any, as may be due to the mortgagor after setting off the mortgage`
  line `debt against the market value of such excess land.`
  line
  line `(7) Where any excess land of a religious or charitable institution vests in the Government, such`
  line `institution shall, in lieu of compensation payable under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) or`
  line `sub-section (3), be paid an annuity equal to the net annual income of the excess land and such net annual`
  line `income shall be determined by the competent authority in the prescribed manner.`
  line
  line `(8) The competent authority shall, after holding an inquiry in the prescribed manner, make an order`
  line `determining the amount of compensation payable to any person under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_144:
  sectionId (37572)
  sectionNo (144)
  orderNo 144
  title `Manner of payment of compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_144_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37572&sectionno=144&orderno=144&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_144_content:
  string
  line `(1) The compensation payable under section 143 shall`
  line `be due from the date of publication of the list under sub-section (3) of section 142 and may paid in cash,`
  line `in a lump sum or in instalments, or in bonds.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the compensation is payable in bonds, the bonds may be made not transferable or`
  line `transferable by endorsement or in any other manner but all such bonds shall be redeemed within such`
  line `period, not exceeding twenty years from the date of issue, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Where there is any delay in the payment of compensation or where the compensation is paid either`
  line `in instalments or in bonds, it shall carry interest at the rate of two and a half per cent. per annum from the`
  line `date on which it falls due.`
obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_145:
  sectionId (37573)
  sectionNo (145)
  orderNo 145
  title `Limit of future acquisition of load.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_145_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37573&sectionno=145&orderno=145&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_145_content:
  string
  line `No person representing a family shall acquire in any`
  line `manner whatsoever, whether by transfer, exchange, lease, agreement or succession, any land where such`
  line `acquisition has the effect of making the total area of the land held by him exceed the ceiling limit; and any`
  line `such land in excess of the ceiling limit shall be treated as excess land of the transferee and provisions of`
  line `section 139 to 144 shall, as far as may be, apply to such excess land.`
obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_146:
  sectionId (37574)
  sectionNo (146)
  orderNo 146
  title `Excess land not to be surrendered in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_146_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37574&sectionno=146&orderno=146&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_146_content:
  string
  line `Where a person representing a family`
  line `holds land not exceeding the ceiling limit, but subsequently the land held exceeds the ceiling limit, then,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in this Chapter, such person shall not be required to surrender any`
  line `part of the land on the ground that it is excess land, if such excess is due to a decrease in the number of`
  line `members of the family.`
obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_147:
  sectionId (37575)
  sectionNo (147)
  orderNo 147
  title `Power of deputy commissioner to take possession of excess land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_147_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37575&sectionno=147&orderno=147&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_147_content:
  string
  line `After the publication of`
  line `the list of excess lands under sub-section (3), of section 142, and after demarcation in the prescribed`
  line `manner of such lands where necessary, the deputy commissioner may take possession of any excess land`
  line `and may use or cause to be used such force as may be necessary for the purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_148:
  sectionId (37576)
  sectionNo (148)
  orderNo 148
  title `Offences and penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_148_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37576&sectionno=148&orderno=148&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_148_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever being bound to submit a return under section 137 fails to`
  line `do so, without reasonable cause, within the prescribed time, or submits a return which he knows or has`
  line `reason to believe to be false, shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever contravenes any lawful order made under this Chapter or otherwise obstructs any person`
  line `from lawfully taking possession of any land shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one`
  line `thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_149:
  sectionId (37577)
  sectionNo (149)
  orderNo 149
  title `Finality of orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_149_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37577&sectionno=149&orderno=149&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_149_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, every order made under this Chapter`
  line `shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_150:
  sectionId (37578)
  sectionNo (150)
  orderNo 150
  title `Power to exempt, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_150_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37578&sectionno=150&orderno=150&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_150_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Administrator may, on an application made to him in this`
  line `behalf within three months from the commencement of this Act, exempt from the operation of`
  line `section 136--`
  line
  line `(a) any land which is being used for growing tea, coffee or rubber including lands used or`
  line `required for use for purposes ancillary to, or for the extension of, the cultivation of tea, coffee or`
  line `rubber to be determined in the prescribed manner;`
  line
  line `(b) any sugarcane farm operated by a sugar factory;`
  line
  line `(c) any specialised farm which is being used for cattle breeding, dairy or wool raising;`
  line
  line `(d) any person who holds a compact block land exceeding the ceiling limit which`
  line
  line `(i) is being used as an orchard from before the 1st day of January, 1958, or`
  line
  line `(ii) is being used as a farm in which heavy investment or permanent structural improvements`
  line `have been made and which, in the opinion of the Administrator, is being so efficiently managed`
  line `that its break up is likely to bring a fall in production:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such person holds the compact block of land together with any other land, he`
  line `shall be permitted to elect to retain either the compact block of land, notwithstanding that it exceeds the`
  line `ceiling limit, or the other land not exceeding the ceiling limit;`
  line
  line `(e) any land which is being held by a co-operative society, provided that where a member of any`
  line `such society holds a share in such land, his share shall be taken into account in determining his ceiling`
  line `limit:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Administrator may entertain the application after the expiry of the said period of`
  line `three months, if he is satisfied that the applicant was prevented by sufficient cause from making the`
  line `application in time.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any land in respect of which exemption has been granted to a person under clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (1) is transferred to another person, the Administrator may, on an application made to him`
  line `within three months from the date of the transfer, exempt the transferee from the operation of section 136`
  line `and section 145 and the provisions of the said clause shall, as far as may be, apply to the grant of such`
  line exemption.
  line
  line `(3) Where the Administrator is of opinion that the use of land for any specified purpose is expedient`
  line `or necessary in the public interest, he may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make a declaration to`
  line `that effect and on the issue of such notification, any person may, notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `section 145 acquire land in excess of the ceiling limit for being used for such specified purpose and such`
  line `person shall, within one month form the date of such acquisition, send intimation thereof to the competent`
  line authority.
  line
  line `(4) Where any land in respect of which exemption has been granted under sub-section (1) or`
  line `sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) ceases to be used, or is not, within the prescribed time, used, for the`
  line `purpose for which exemption had been granted, the Administrator may, after giving the persons affected`
  line `an opportunity of being heard, withdraw such exemption.`
obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_151:
  sectionId (37579)
  sectionNo (151)
  orderNo 151
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_151_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37579&sectionno=151&orderno=151&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_151_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of this Chapter,--`
  line
  line `(a) "holding" means the aggregate area of land held by a person as a landowner;`
  line
  line `(b) "fragment" means a holding of less than two and a half acres in area;`
  line
  line `(c) "land" has the same meaning as in Chapter XI.`
obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_152:
  sectionId (37580)
  sectionNo (152)
  orderNo 152
  title `Restrictions on transfer, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_152_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37580&sectionno=152&orderno=152&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_152_content:
  string
  line `(1) No portion of a holding shall be transferred by way of sale,`
  line `exchange, gift, bequest or mortgage with possession, so as to create a fragment:`
  line
  line `Provided that the provisions of this sub-section shall not apply to a gift made in favour of the`
  line `Bhoodan movement initiated by Acharya Vinoba Bhave.`
  line
  line `(2) No portion of a holding shall be transferred by way of lease, where as a result of such lease,--`
  line
  line `(i) the lessor shall be left with less than two and a half acres, or`
  line
  line `(ii) the total area held by the lessee exceeds the limit of a family holding.`
  line
  line `(3) No fragment shall be transferred to a person who does not have some land under personal`
  line `cultivation, or to a person who holds, or by reason of such transfer shall hold, land in excess of the limit`
  line `of a family holding.`
obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_153:
  sectionId (37581)
  sectionNo (153)
  orderNo 153
  title `Partition of holding.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_153_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37581&sectionno=153&orderno=153&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_153_content:
  string
  line `(1) No holding shall be partitioned in such manner as to create a`
  line fragment.
  line
  line `(2) A fragment shall not be partitioned unless as a result of such partition its portions get merged in`
  line `holdings of two and a half acres or more or in fragments so as to create holdings of two and a half acres or`
  line more;
  line
  line `(3) Whenever, in a suit for partition, the court finds that the partition of a holding will result in the`
  line `creation of a fragment, the court shall, instead of proceeding to divide the holding, direct the sale of the`
  line `same and distribute the proceeds thereof among the co-sharers.`
  line
  line `(4) Whenever a holding is put up for sale under sub-section (3), a co-sharer shall have the first option`
  line `to purchase the holding at the highest bid; if there are two or more co-sharers claiming the first option,`
  line `that co-sharer who offers the highest consideration shall be preferred.`
obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_154:
  sectionId (37582)
  sectionNo (154)
  orderNo 154
  title `Transfers in contravention of this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_154_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37582&sectionno=154&orderno=154&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_154_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any transfer, partition or lease of land made`
  line `in contravention of the provisions of this Chapter shall be void.`
  line
  line `(2) No document of transfer, partition or lease shall be registered unless declarations in writing are`
  line `made, in such form and manner as may be prescribed, by the parties thereto before the competent`
  line `registering authority under the Indian Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908), regarding lands held by each`
  line `prior to the transaction and the land which shall come to hold thereafter.`
  line
  line `(3) No registering authority shall register under the Indian Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908), any`
  line `document of transfer, partition or lease of land if, from the declarations made under sub-section (2), it`
  line `appears that the transaction has been effected in contravention of the provisions of this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_155:
  sectionId (37583)
  sectionNo (155)
  orderNo 155
  title Penalty.
  content obj_root_law_sections_155_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37583&sectionno=155&orderno=155&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_155_content:
  string
  line `The parties to any transfer, partition or lease made or entered into in contravention of`
  line `any of the provisions of this Chapter shall be punishable with fine which extend to one hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_156:
  sectionId (37584)
  sectionNo (156)
  orderNo 156
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_156_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37584&sectionno=156&orderno=156&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_156_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Administrator may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to carry out the purposes of this Part.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the form in which and the period within which a return under section 137 may be submitted;`
  line
  line `(b) the agency through which information may be collected under section 138;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner of holding enquiries under this Part;`
  line
  line `(d) the matters which may be determined under sub-section (1) of section 139 and the manner of`
  line `determination of excess lands under this Part;`
  line
  line `(e) the form in which a list under sub-section (3) of section 139 or sub-section (3) of section 142`
  line `may be prepared and the manner of publication of such list;`
  line
  line `(f) the period within which an application for registration of excess land may be made under the`
  line `proviso to sub-section (4) of section 141;`
  line
  line `(g) the manner of apportionment of compensation between the landowner and the tenant under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 143;`
  line
  line `(h) the manner of assessment of the market value of any structure of building or trees under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 143;`
  line
  line `(i) the manner of recovery of the compensation payable the tenant under sub-section (5) of`
  line `section 143;`
  line
  line `(j) the manner of determining under sub-section (6) of section 143 the market value of any excess`
  line `land over which a mortgagee in possession acquires the rights of the mortgagor;`
  line
  line `(k) the manner of determination of the net annual income of any excess land for the purpose of`
  line `payment of compensation under section 143;`
  line
  line `(l) the manner of payment of compensation including the number of instalments in which the`
  line `compensation may be paid or recovered and the period within which bonds may be redeemed;`
  line
  line `(m) the manner of demarcation of any excess land under section 147;`
  line
  line `(n) the matters which may be determined by the Administrator in granting an exemption under`
  line `section 150 including the form in which applications and intimations may be made or given, under`
  line `section 150;`
  line
  line `(o) the from of declarations under section 154;`
  line
  line `(p) any other matter which is to be or may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_157:
  sectionId (37585)
  sectionNo (157)
  orderNo 157
  title `Recovery of amounts due as an arrear of and revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_157_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37585&sectionno=157&orderno=157&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_157_content:
  string
  line `Without prejudice to any other`
  line `provision of this Act, any amount due to the Government, whether by way of costs, penalty or otherwise,`
  line `and any other amount which is ordered to be paid to or recovered by the Government, under this Act shall`
  line `be recoverable in the same manner as an arrear of land revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_158:
  sectionId (37586)
  sectionNo (158)
  orderNo 158
  title `Special provision regarding Scheduled Tribes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_158_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37586&sectionno=158&orderno=158&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_158_content:
  string
  line `No transfer of land by a person who is a`
  line `member of the Scheduled Tribes shall be valid unless--`
  line
  line `(a) the transfer is to another member of the Scheduled Tribes; or`
  line
  line `(b) where the transfer is to a person who is not a member of any such tribe, it is made with the`
  line `previous permission in writing of the deputy commissioner; or`
  line
  line `(c) the transfer is by way of mortgage to a co-operative society.`
obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_159:
  sectionId (37587)
  sectionNo (159)
  orderNo 159
  title `Jurisdiction of civil courts excluded.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_159_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37587&sectionno=159&orderno=159&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_159_content:
  string
  line `No suit or other proceedings shall, unless otherwise`
  line `expressly provided for in this Act or in any other law for the time being in force, lie or be instituted in any`
  line `civil court with respect to any matter arising under the provided for by this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that if in a dispute between parties a question of title is involved, a civil suit may be brought`
  line `for the adjudication of such question.`
obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_160:
  sectionId (37588)
  sectionNo (160)
  orderNo 160
  title `Act to over-ride contract and other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_160_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37588&sectionno=160&orderno=160&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_160_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided, the provisions of this`
  line `Act shall have effect notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained as any other law, custom or`
  line `usage or agreement or decree or order of court.`
obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_161:
  sectionId (37589)
  sectionNo (161)
  orderNo 161
  title Court-fees.
  content obj_root_law_sections_161_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37589&sectionno=161&orderno=161&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_161_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Court-fees Act, 1870 (7 of 1870) every`
  line `application, appeal or other proceeding under this Act shall bear a court-fee stamp of such value as may`
  line `be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_162:
  sectionId (37590)
  sectionNo (162)
  orderNo 162
  title `Village officers to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_162_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_162_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37590&sectionno=162&orderno=162&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_162_content:
  string
  line `Every amin and every other village officer appointed`
  line `under this Act shall be deemed to be a public servant within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal`
  line `Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_162_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_163:
  sectionId (37591)
  sectionNo (163)
  orderNo 163
  title `Power to exempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_163_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_163_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37591&sectionno=163&orderno=163&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_163_content:
  string
  line `With the previous approval of the Government, the Administrator may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette exempt any class of lands from all or any of the provision of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_163_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_164:
  sectionId (37592)
  sectionNo (164)
  orderNo 164
  title `General provision as to penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_164_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_164_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37592&sectionno=164&orderno=164&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_164_content:
  string
  line `Whoever contravenes any provision of this Act for which`
  line `no penalty has been otherwise provided for therein shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five`
  line `hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_164_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_165:
  sectionId (37593)
  sectionNo (165)
  orderNo 165
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_165_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_165_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37593&sectionno=165&orderno=165&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_165_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other proceedings shall lie--`
  line
  line `(a) against any officer of the Government for anything in good faith done or intended to be done`
  line `under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) against the Government for any damage caused or likely to caused or any injury suffered or`
  line `likely to be suffered by anything, in good faith, done or intended to be done under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_165_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_166:
  sectionId (37594)
  sectionNo (166)
  orderNo 166
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_166_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_166_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37594&sectionno=166&orderno=166&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_166_content:
  string
  line `The Administrator may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `delegate to any officer or authority subordinate to him any of the powers conferred on him or on any`
  line `officer subordinate to him by this Act, other than the power to make rules, to be exercised subject to such`
  line `restrictions and conditions as may be specified in the said notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_166_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_167:
  sectionId (37595)
  sectionNo (167)
  orderNo 167
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_167_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_167_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37595&sectionno=167&orderno=167&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_167_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in giving effect to any provision of this`
  line `Act, the Government may, as occasion requires, take any action not inconsistent with the provisions of`
  line `this Act which may appear to it necessary for the purpose of removing the difficulty.`
obj_root_law_sections_167_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_168:
  sectionId (37596)
  sectionNo (168)
  orderNo 168
  title `General power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_168_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_168_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37596&sectionno=168&orderno=168&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_168_content:
  string
  line `Without prejudice to any power to make rules contained`
  line `elsewhere in this Act, the Administrator may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules generally`
  line `to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_168_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_169:
  sectionId (37597)
  sectionNo (169)
  orderNo 169
  title `Laying of rules before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_169_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_169_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37597&sectionno=169&orderno=169&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_169_content:
  string
  line `Every rule made under this Act shall be laid as soon as`
  line `may be after it is made before each House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty`
  line `days which may be comprised in one session or in two successive sessions, and if before the expiry of the`
  line `session in which it is so laid or the session immediately following, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rules should not be made, the rule shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so however that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `the rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_169_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_170:
  sectionId (37598)
  sectionNo (170)
  orderNo 170
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_170_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_170_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501&sectionId=37598&sectionno=170&orderno=170&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00002_196033_1517807318501
obj_root_law_sections_170_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the date on which any of the provisions of This Act are`
  line `brought into force in any area in the Union territory of Manipur, the enactments specified in the Schedule`
  line `or so much thereof as relate to the matters covered by the provisions so brought into force shall stand`
  line `repealed in such area.`
  line
  line `(2) The repeal of any enactment or part thereof by sub-section (1) shall not affect,--`
  line
  line `(a) the previous operation of such enactment or anything duly done or suffered thereunder;`
  line
  line `(b) any right, privilege, obligation or liability acquired, accrued or incurred under such enactment;`
  line
  line `(c) any penalty, forfeiture or punishment incurred in respect of any offence committed against`
  line `such enactment;`
  line
  line `(d) any investigation legal proceeding or remedy in respect of any such right, privilege,`
  line `obligation, liability, penalty, forfeiture or punishment as aforesaid,`
  line
  line `and any such investigation, legal proceeding or remedy may be instituted or enforced and any such`
  line `penalty, forfeiture or punishment may be imposed as if such enactment or part thereof had not been`
  line repealed.
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions contained in sub-section (2), any appointment, rule, order, notification or`
  line `proclamation made or issued, any lease, rent, right or liability granted, fixed, acquired or incurred and any`
  line `other thing done or action taken under any of the enactments or parts thereof repealed under`
  line `sub-section (1) shall, in so far as it is not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act brought into force,`
  line `be deemed to have been made, issued, granted, fixed, acquired, incurred, done or taken under this Act and`
  line `shall continue to be in force until superseded by anything done or any action taken under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) Any custom or usage prevailing at the time any of the provisions of this Act are brought into force`
  line `in any area in Union territory of Manipur and having the force of law therein shall, if such custom or`
  line `usage is repugnant to or inconsistent with such provision, cease to be operative to the extent of such`
  line `repugnancy or inconsistency.`
